review_text: Caminata de dificultad leve, 45 minutos haciendolo despacio. Algo de pendiente pero es facil. Mirador muy lindo, para ir con el mate. Se accede por el mismo camino que lleva a bosque de arrayanes. En un punto esta indicado el desvio hacia este mirador y el otro que te muestra bahia mansa. Vale la pena!
review_translated_text: Walk of mild difficulty, 45 minutes doing it slowly. Some slope but its easy. Very nice viewpoint, to go with the mate. It is accessed by the same path that leads to the myrtle forest. At one point the detour to this viewpoint is indicated and the other shows you Bahia Mansa. Its worth it!

review_text: Hermosa caminata entre el bosque...fuimos con un bebe y es bastante empinada pero vale la pena el esfuerzo para subir y deleitar la vista.
review_translated_text: Beautiful hike through the forest...we went with a baby and it is quite steep but it is worth the effort to climb and delight the view.

review_text: Hermosas vistas de las bahias y el lago. Sin duda recomendable. Hay un poco de subida pero se hace tranquilamente.
review_translated_text: Beautiful views of the bays and the lake. Without a doubt recommended. There is a bit of a climb but it is done calmly.

review_text: Very nice trail with places to sit and when you reach the Bahia Mansa viewpoint the view dazzles you!! Ideal place for those who enjoy a good walk. You can also access the other Bahia Brava viewpoint via another short trail, both of which are free to enter.

Es un trekking corto de unos dos kilometros y medio ida y vuelta, en tiempos de caminata.  Nosotros fuimos solo al mirador del Brazo Norte, que tienen una excelente vista. Los banos de la entrada , que pertenece a Parques Nacionales estaban clausurados nada que nos extrane, despues de todo es la Argentina. De todos modos, el paseo vale la pena.

Una maravilla natural. Verdadera belleza. Los carteles indicativos estaban algo deteriorados, pero no es un gran problema. Es sendero es claro y seguro, con los recaudos necesarios. Recomendable llevar ropa comoda y agua si es epoca de calor.
review_translated_text: A natural wonder. True beauty. The indicative signs were somewhat damaged, but it is not a big problem. The path is clear and safe, with the necessary precautions. It is advisable to wear comfortable clothing and water if it is hot weather.

review_text: Bellisimo lugar, se llega partiendo del sendero que va al bosque de Arrayanes en el puerto, esta a 1 km aprox, pero es todo el tramo de subida, igualmente vale la pena ir. Son 2 miradores a los que se llega por el mismo sendero, en uno se observa la Bahia Mansa y en el otro la Bahia Brava. Tienen carteles de senalizacion para llegar. Si uno realiza solo ese tramo no se paga entrada al parque
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, you get there starting from the path that goes to the Arrayanes forest in the port, it is approximately 1 km away, but it is all uphill, it is still worth going. There are 2 viewpoints that can be reached by the same path, in one you can see Mansa Bay and in the other you can see Brava Bay. They have signposts to get there. If you do only that section, you do not pay entrance to the park.

review_text: Es absolutamente increble el mirador, si tenes suerte hasta ves pasar truchas. En primavera es hermoso, pero en cualquier estacion merece que la visiten, es un paraiso.
review_translated_text: The viewpoint is absolutely incredible, if you are lucky you even see trout passing by. In spring it is beautiful, but in any season it is worth a visit, it is a paradise.

review_text: Absolutely beautiful and worth visiting!! You get there through parque arrayanes, start in the path to bosque de arrayanes and theres a detour. Overall ~3km uphill Visited on

Luego de una caminata de unos veinte minutos se accede A este mirador maravilloso. El paseo por el bosque frondoso es ya algo que vale la pena. Pero luego del esfuerzo se llega a este hermoso punto donde se puede apreciar desde lo alto una increible vista del Nahuel Huapi. Vale la pena realizarlo. Y luego ir al mirador de Bahia Mansa que son 5 minutos mas por el mismo sendero.
review_translated_text: After a walk of about twenty minutes you access this wonderful viewpoint. The walk through the lush forest is already something worth it. But after the effort you reach this beautiful point where you can see an incredible view of Nahuel Huapi from above. It is worth doing it. And then go to the Bahia Mansa viewpoint which is 5 more minutes along the same path.

review_text: Hermosa vista y lugar maravilloso para pasar un rato.
review_translated_text: Beautiful view and wonderful place to spend some time.

review_text: Lindo lugar a este mirardor se llega por el sendero del bosque de los arrayanes, a unos 900 metros de arrancar el sendero, encontramos 2 miradores(mirador de bahi mansa y mirardor de bahia brava) el acceso hasta este lugar es gratis!
review_translated_text: A nice place to reach this viewpoint through the Arrayanes forest trail, about 900 meters from the start of the trail, we find 2 viewpoints (Bahi Mansa viewpoint and Bahia Brava viewpoint) access to this place is free!

review_text: No es un Mirador, es un Balcon,si puedes el mejor momento es el atardecer. Podes conocerlo entrando por la entrada Istmo Quetrihuel, y haces 1 km , ascendiendo, o de regreso de la caminata de los Arrayanes.la entrada esta ubicada entre los dos puertos, y tiene juegos, banos muy limpios y acceso a las dos playas brava y mansa, imperdibles, ideal para pasar el dia!! Especialmente con chicos
review_translated_text: It is not a Mirador, it is a Balcony, if you can the best time is at sunset. You can visit it by entering through the Istmo Quetrihuel entrance, and do 1 km, ascending, or returning from the Arrayanes walk. The entrance is located between the two ports, and has games, very clean bathrooms and access to the two beaches Brava and tame, unmissable, ideal to spend the day!! Especially with boys

review_text: Lo mas hermoso que vi en mi vida. Imperdible, desde este punto se pueden apreciar todos los cerros del lado norte. El sendero son aprox 1km de caminata ida, cuesta un poco hacerlo pero hay troncos para sentarse y recuperarse. Vi que se puede hacer en bicicleta, un poco mas dificil. La caminata hasta el bosque de arrayanes es de 11km ida (se debe abonar entrada al parque)
review_translated_text: The most beautiful thing I saw in my life. Not to be missed, from this point you can see all the hills on the north side. The trail is approximately 1km one way, it is a bit difficult to do but there are logs to sit on and recover. I saw that it can be done by bicycle, a little more difficult. The walk to the myrtle forest is 11km one way (you must pay an entrance fee to the park)

review_text: Hermoso lugar. La paz que hay es increible y magica. La vista es impresionante. Vale la pena el esfuerzo para subir.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. The peace there is is incredible and magical. The view is impressive. It is worth the effort to climb.

review_text: Una subida un poco exigente en la primera parte, pero solo lleva entre 20 y 30 llegar. La vista es aun mas linda que la del otro mirador (el de bahia mansa), que esta conectado a este a traves de un sendero sencillo. Un muy lindo paseo con una vista sublime.
review_translated_text: A slightly demanding climb in the first part, but it only takes between 20 and 30 to get there. The view is even prettier than the other viewpoint (that of Bahia Mansa), which is connected to it through a simple path. A very nice walk with a sublime view.

review_text: Lindo lugar con 2 vistas increibles .. especial para hacer caminata y disfrutar la tarde !!!
review_translated_text: Nice place with 2 incredible views.. special for hiking and enjoying the afternoon!!!

review_text: Hermoso  mirador que se ingresa sin pagar. Esta a pocos minutos de la entrada al parque
review_translated_text: Beautiful viewpoint that you enter without paying. It is just a few minutes from the entrance to the park.

review_text: Vale la pena subir, la vista es imponente, aunque recomiendo ir al otro, Mirador Brazo Norte (mucho mas linda vista)
review_translated_text: It is worth going up, the view is impressive, although I recommend going to the other one, Mirador Brazo Norte (much prettier view)

review_text: Un lugar maravilloso. Se accede con una breve caminata en subida que vale totalmente la pena.
review_translated_text: A wonderful place. It is accessed with a short uphill walk that is totally worth it.

review_text: Llegamos, ardua la subida pero vale la pena.
review_translated_text: We arrive, the climb is arduous but it is worth it.

review_text: A beautiful viewpoint of the entire bay and beyond, a path of medium difficulty, sometimes uphill and sometimes downhill. But short of journey. The photos from there cant go wrong with such a view!!
Espectacular, la vista es increible (sobre todo la de brazo norte) y esta a escasos 45 minutos de la entrada al parque/itsmo
review_translated_text: Spectacular, the view is incredible (especially the north arm) and it is just 45 minutes from the entrance to the park/isthmus

review_text: Sorprendidos!!! Alli en Villa La Angostura, en una caminata con  dificultad baja a media, llegamos a los Miradores de la Bahias Mansa y Brava.  IMPERDIBLES!!! Nos quedamos alli en la ciudad, a almorzar, hermoso centro, con muchas alternativas gastronomicas.  Muy bella Ciudad, de lo mejor del circuito de los 7 lagos.  MARAVILLOSO!!!
review_translated_text: Surprised!!! There in Villa La Angostura, on a walk with low to medium difficulty, we arrived at the Mansa and Brava Bay Viewpoints. UNMISSABLE!!! We stayed there in the city, for lunch, beautiful center, with many gastronomic alternatives. Very beautiful city, one of the best of the 7 lakes circuit. MARVELOUS!!!

review_text: Un lugar excelente para sentarse a disfrutar de la vista y ver los atardeceres. un poco ventoso pero hermoso lugar
review_translated_text: An excellent place to sit and enjoy the view and watch the sunsets. a little windy but beautiful place

review_text: Por que ceve toda las Villa de desde ai y muy lindo
review_translated_text: Why do you see all the Villas from here and very nice

review_text: Pure nature! Bring mate to spend some time there contemplating this wonder!!! Its worth it!!!! Safety pin!
Hermoso mirador que se sube desde el Puerto de Bahia Mansa, y tiene un sendero que te lleva al Bosque de Arrayanes.
review_translated_text: Beautiful viewpoint that goes up from the Puerto de Bahia Mansa, and has a path that takes you to the Arrayanes Forest.

review_text: En un paseo corto y para toda la familia se puede llegar luego de un poco de esfuerzo a este gran mirador, uno de los dos mas cercanos del Parque
review_translated_text: In a short walk and for the whole family you can reach this great viewpoint, one of the two closest in the Park, after a little effort.

review_text: Vista completa de los cerros. Acceso empinado pero vale la pena!
review_translated_text: Complete view of the hills. Steep access but worth it!

review_text: Uno de los miradores mas lindos del recorrido.
review_translated_text: One of the most beautiful viewpoints on the tour.

review_text: Vale la pena aun si llueve o hace frio no se siente dentro del bosque..Imperdible!!!
review_translated_text: It is worth it even if it rains or is cold you dont feel inside the forest... Unmissable!!!

review_text: Muy linda vista
review_translated_text: Very nice view

review_text: Hermosa vista!!! Lugar super tranquilo para disfrutar de la naturaleza!
review_translated_text: Beautiful view!!! Super quiet place to enjoy nature!

review_text: Muy lindo lugar. Vale la pena despues de una buena subida.
review_translated_text: Very nice place. Its worth it after a good climb.

review_text: simplemente hermoso .vale la pena la caminata
review_translated_text: simply beautiful. worth the walk

review_text: Muy lindo, esta dentro del Parque, requiere un pequeno esfuerzo para llegar por el sendero perfectamente marcado, 1 hora aprox para subir, vale la pena, Si subes en silencio los pajaros te acompanan con su canto de vez en cuando.
review_translated_text: Very nice, it is inside the Park, it requires a little effort to get there along the perfectly marked path, approximately 1 hour to go up, it is worth it. If you go up in silence the birds accompany you with their song from time to time.

review_text: Paz absoluta, vista increible
review_translated_text: Absolute peace, incredible view

review_text: Es precioso por el mismo sendero que vas al Bosque de Arrayanes tenes desvio y te vas a los dos Miradores  Brazo Norte y Bahia Mansa  en uno ves ambas bahias el otro orienta hacia los Andes y el Nahuel Huapi.  No podes perderte de ver algo tan imponente y Hermoso.
review_translated_text: It is beautiful along the same path that you go to the Arrayanes Forest, you have a detour and you go to the two Viewpoints Brazo Norte and Bahia Mansa in one you see both bays, the other faces towards the Andes and Nahuel Huapi. You cant miss seeing something so impressive and beautiful.

review_text: Incomparable belleza!!! El color del agua es irreal, vibrante. La playa es hermosa, ideal para pasar la tarde.
review_translated_text: Incomparable beauty!!! The color of the water is unreal, vibrant. The beach is beautiful, ideal for spending the afternoon.

review_text: Increible!!! Una de las mejores vistas
review_translated_text: Incredible!!! One of the best views

review_text: This viewpoint is reaching 700 meters of ascent! There is a path to the left, and then the path divides into two inns, this is the one on the right. It costs a lot for those who are not used to it. But the view is worth it!!!
Muy buena caminata para llegar
review_translated_text: Very good hike to get there

review_text: Majestuoso, es un camino de 1km con 100mts de desnivel. Se puede entrar hasta las 16hs Es una dificultad media, lo indica en la entrada pero muchos lo ignoran y terminan desistiendo a medio camino.
review_translated_text: Majestic, it is a 1km path with 100 meters of elevation gain. You can enter until 4:00 p.m. It is a medium difficulty, it indicates it at the entrance but many ignore it and end up giving up halfway.

review_text: Un lugar sonado. Vista espectacular
review_translated_text: A dream place. Spectacular view

review_text: La vista es imponente, no hay foto que le haga justicia, hay que verlo en persona. Se ve la isla Fray Menendez y de fondo varios cerros.
review_translated_text: The view is impressive, there is no photo that does it justice, you have to see it in person. You can see Fray Menendez Island and several hills in the background.

review_text: Excellent! Don t be afraid by the sign about the entrance fees - the path to the viewpoints (there s two) is free (the fee is for going deeper into the park)

Mirador mas ventoso. La vista es maravillosa. El ascenso es por sendero generalmente angosto; hay que estar atento a la pisada porque es resbaladizo. Pero es muy interesante, bellas vistas, y fluyen las emociones. Sobre todo cuando cumpliste el objetivo.
review_translated_text: Windiest viewpoint. The view is wonderful. The ascent is along a generally narrow path; You have to be careful with your footing because it is slippery. But it is very interesting, beautiful views, and emotions flow. Especially when you met the goal.

review_text: Frente al mirados de Bahia Mansa en La Angostura se ve esta vista que expreaa visualmente el nombre de La Villa
review_translated_text: In front of the Bahia Mansa viewpoint in La Angostura you can see this view that visually expresses the name of La Villa

review_text: Hermoso. Poco cuidado todo el sendero. Partes poco seguras. Cansador para el q no esta acostumbrado a estos desafios. Llevar agua y subir despacio si no estas entrenado. No ir si hay mucho viento.
review_translated_text: Beautiful. The entire trail is poorly maintained. Unsafe parts. Tiring for those who are not used to these challenges. Carry water and climb slowly if you are not trained. Dont go if there is a lot of wind.

review_text: Muy bello lugar. Se llega caminando desde la entrada de bosque de arrayanes. 30/40 minutos aprox de caminata en montana y partes de camino de cornisa.
review_translated_text: Very beautiful place. It is reached by walking from the entrance to the myrtle forest. Approximately 30/40 minutes of mountain walking and parts of the cornice path.

review_text: Increible vista! Esta ubicado dentro de parque nacional de los ARRAYANES, muy hermosa vista a bahia brava y el lago Nahuel Huapi. Suele haber mucho viento. El camino son unos 900 metros faciles con subidas y bajadas, se tarda unos 20 o 30 minutos en llegar.
review_translated_text: Amazing view! It is located within the ARRAYANES National Park, with a very beautiful view of Bahia Brava and Lake Nahuel Huapi. There is usually a lot of wind. The path is about 900 easy meters with ups and downs, it takes about 20 or 30 minutes to get there.

review_text: Increible!!! No tienen que dejar de ir a este mirador. El camino para llegar a este tambien es muy lindo.
review_translated_text: Incredible!!! You dont have to miss going to this viewpoint. The path to get there is also very nice.

review_text: Vistas increibles del lago y las montanas.
review_translated_text: Incredible views of the lake and mountains.

review_text: Cuesta llegar hasta arriba, pero vale la pena el esfuerzo!!! Imperdible!!!
review_translated_text: Its hard to get to the top, but its worth the effort!!! Safety pin!!!

review_text: Su nombre real es Mirador Brazo Norte y hay que hacer aproximadamente 1km por el sendero al bosque de Arrayanes para llegar a la bifurcacion a los miradores. Una vez en la bifurcacion, el sendero vuelve aproximadamente 400 metros hasta llegar hasta al mirador el cual de encuentra correctamente vallado. La visita es obligada, la vista impagable. Para una mejor experiencia, ir con dia despejado.
review_translated_text: Its real name is Mirador Brazo Norte and you have to walk approximately 1km along the path to the Arrayanes forest to reach the fork at the viewpoints. Once at the fork, the path returns approximately 400 meters until it reaches the viewpoint which is correctly fenced. The visit is a must, the view is priceless. For a better experience, go on a clear day.

review_text: Hermoso... Bello... Increible...
review_translated_text: Beautiful... Beautiful... Incredible...

review_text: La belleza es increible vale la pena el esfuerzo de subir lo unico que me parecio mal que el ingreso por la oficina de APN tiene los banos clausurados
review_translated_text: The beauty is incredible, it is worth the effort to climb the only thing that seemed bad to me is that the entrance through the APN office has the bathrooms closed

review_text: Hermoso lugar !! Vale la pena hacerlo
review_translated_text: Beautiful place !! Its worth doing

review_text: Hermoso lugar. Seguro y de facil acceso.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. Safe and easy access.

review_text: Bellisimo...no te lo pierdas si venis a villa langostura
review_translated_text: Beautiful...dont miss it if you come to Villa Langostura

review_text: Totalmente recomendable llegar a este mirador y tomarse un buen momento para disfrutar de la espectacular vista que nos regala. Imponente! Paisajes increibles, recuerdos inolvidables.
review_translated_text: It is totally recommended to get to this viewpoint and take a good moment to enjoy the spectacular view it gives us. Imposing! Incredible landscapes, unforgettable memories.

review_text: Hermoso paisaje!!! No se lo pierdan!!
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape!!! Do not miss it!!

review_text: Hermosas las vistas, lugares encantadores, unas fotos increibles.
review_translated_text: Beautiful views, charming places, incredible photos.

review_text: Hermosa Vista!
review_translated_text: Beautiful view!

review_text: Lugar de indescriptible belleza, muy recomendable subir si visita Villa La Angostura. Son 2 kms de sendero muy bien senalizado.
review_translated_text: Place of indescribable beauty, highly recommended to go up if you visit Villa La Angostura. There are 2 km of very well marked trail.

review_text: Una de las Bahias que conforman al Itsmo de Quetrihue por donde se accede por un sendero 11km  de bosque al bosque de Arrayanes  . . Hermoso treking. Dificultad media, se hace bien en 3 horas.
review_translated_text: One of the bays that make up the Quetrihue Isthmus where you can access the Arrayanes forest through an 11km forest path. . Beautiful trekking. Medium difficulty, done well in 3 hours.

review_text: Esta a unos 10 minutos de caminata por el parque de Arrayanes. Se llega por la bajada que esta hacia la izquierda del camino de los miradores. Muy hermosa vista, imperdible!
review_translated_text: It is about a 10-minute walk through the Arrayanes park. It is reached by the descent that is to the left of the path to the viewpoints. Very beautiful view, unmissable!

review_text: Muy linda vista
review_translated_text: Very nice view

review_text: Hacer el camino de vuelta desde el bosque de arrayanes a pie o en bicicleta.
review_translated_text: Make the way back from the myrtle forest on foot or by bicycle.

review_text: Bellisimo lugar !
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!

review_text: La mejor vista de la region, te hace sentir en otro mundo. Es un poco cansado llegar pero vale la pena
review_translated_text: The best view in the region, makes you feel in another world. Its a little tiring to get there but its worth it.

review_text: Una panoramica del Nahuel huapi y su cordon montanoso, no se puede estar en angostura y no ir a estos puntos panoramicos. Una caminata de 20 minutos con la naturaleza y un final bien premediado
review_translated_text: A panoramic view of Nahuel Huapi and its mountain range, you cannot be in Angostura and not go to these panoramic points. A 20-minute walk with nature and a well-prepared ending

review_text: Hermoso!
review_translated_text: Beautiful!

review_text: Hermoso! Un ascenso un poco mas fuerte al principio pero amigable en generak. En 20 se llega a uno de los dos miradores. En este caso, el de Bahia Brava. Si vas en bici, ojo! xq hay que cargarla hasta llegar a la bifurcacion donde se elige si ir hasta la punta de la peninsula (bosque de arrayanes, 11km) o subir a los miradores ( aprox 700m a c/u,) Todas las opciones son imperdibles! Por supuesto que existen paseos en barco que te llevan al bosque de arrayanes ($700 promo saliendo de Bahia mansa y $1000 saliendo de Bahia Brava. Ida y vuelta + 1h de estadia)
review_translated_text: Beautiful! A slightly steeper climb at the beginning but generally friendly. In 20 you reach one of the two viewpoints. In this case, Bahia Brava. If you go by bike, be careful! Because you have to carry it until you reach the fork where you choose whether to go to the tip of the peninsula (myrtle forest, 11km) or go up to the viewpoints (approximately 700m each), All options are unmissable! Of course there are boat trips that take you to the myrtle forest ($700 promo leaving from Bahia Mansa and $1000 leaving from Bahia Brava. Round trip + 1 hour stay)

review_text: Great hike!
Una belleza total no se la pierdan
review_translated_text: A total beauty, dont miss it

review_text: Uno de los dos miradores a la entrada de la peninsula Quetrihue. Los dos son imponentes y cada uno es increible a su manera.
review_translated_text: One of the two viewpoints at the entrance to the Quetrihue peninsula. They are both impressive and each one is incredible in their own way.

review_text: Beautiful viewpoint! I remember that you had to walk quite a bit and with a slope to get to it, but nothing too difficult and it is really worth it!
Este mirador es muy bello. Se accede por la peninsula de quetrihue. En el recorrido un se puede ver tanto la bahia mansa como la brava. Todas las opciones valen la pena.
review_translated_text: This viewpoint is very beautiful. It is accessed through the Quetrihue peninsula. On the tour you can see both the gentle and brave bays. All options are worth it.

review_text: Actualmente (20/10/2021) el sendero al mirador esta cerrado. He ido anos anteriores y es una vista hermosa.
review_translated_text: Currently (10/20/2021) the path to the viewpoint is closed. Ive been there in previous years and its a beautiful sight.

review_text: Prepararse para la subida ! Porque no se lo pueden perder. La vista es espectacular
review_translated_text: Prepare for the climb! Because they cant miss it. The view is spectacular

review_text: Experiencia increible
review_translated_text: Incredible experience

review_text: Excellent view!!! I recommend walking up here more than taking the boat trip to the arrayanes forest, the walkway is very short. There are not many myrtle trees. I do not recommend it.
Una panoramica magnifica. Si se llega hasta alli conviene visitar tambien el otro mirador.
review_translated_text: A magnificent panorama. If you get there, you should also visit the other viewpoint.

review_text: Es un lugar de ensueno, tener en cuenta la pendiente hacia arriba para ir. Visita infaltable!
review_translated_text: It is a dream place, keep in mind the upward slope to go. Unmissable visit!

review_text: Increible la vista
review_translated_text: Incredible view

review_text: Una belleza. Pero hay que caminar un buen rato
review_translated_text: A beauty. But you have to walk for a while

review_text: Se puede ir a caminar (1km aprox) sin costo, el camino por el parque son 12.5km y se abona. Muy economico
review_translated_text: You can go for a walk (approximately 1km) for free, the walk through the park is 12.5km and there is a fee. Very economical

review_text: Precioso. El ascenso hasta el mirador cansa pero vale el esfuerzo, la panoramica es increible.
review_translated_text: Precious. The climb to the viewpoint is tiring but worth the effort, the panoramic view is incredible.

review_text: Muy lindo mirador. Desde el itsmo toma 1 hora el sendero para ir a los dos miradores
review_translated_text: Very nice viewpoint. From the isthmus the path takes 1 hour to go to the two viewpoints

review_text: Muy linda vista, pero los turistas no cuidan los lugares y no hay mantenimiento
review_translated_text: Very nice view, but tourists do not take care of the places and there is no maintenance

review_text: Se encuentra este mirador en el Istmo de arrayanes. Hay que hacer un sendero de dificultad media.
review_translated_text: This viewpoint is located on the Isthmus of Arrayanes. You have to do a path of medium difficulty.

review_text: Hermoso. Dificultad minima para llegar.
review_translated_text: Beautiful. Minimal difficulty to get there.

review_text: Imperdible!
review_translated_text: Safety pin!

review_text: Igual dificultad ambos miradores. Baja tirando a media (hay repecho). Muy buena vista
review_translated_text: Equal difficulty for both viewpoints. Go down halfway (there is a slope). Really nice view

review_text: Un lugar majestuoso
review_translated_text: A majestic place

review_text: An incredible view!!!!! It is easy to get there... of low difficulty... Wonderful landscapes...
Imperdible lugar, facil de llegar, muy bien marcado el sendero
review_translated_text: Unmissable place, easy to get to, very well marked trail

review_text: Inolvidable!
review_translated_text: Unforgettable!

review_text: Hermosa caminata para llegar a una vista espectacular
review_translated_text: Beautiful hike to reach a spectacular view

review_text: Imperdibles vistas desde este mirador.
review_translated_text: Unmissable views from this viewpoint.

review_text: Hermosa vista!!!! La caminata entre los arboles en medio del bosque es una experiencia fantastica!!!
review_translated_text: Beautiful view!!!! The walk between the trees in the middle of the forest is a fantastic experience!!!

review_text: Hermoso, se puede hacer con ninos pero hay que ir despacio y llevar agua
review_translated_text: Beautiful, it can be done with children but you have to go slowly and bring water

review_text: Increible lugar, facil acceso, subida continua al principio pero vale el esfuerzo.
review_translated_text: Incredible place, easy access, continuous climb at the beginning but worth the effort.

review_text: Junto con el Mirador de Bahia Mansa es uno de los lugares mas bellos q he visto. El recorrido fantastico
review_translated_text: Together with the Bahia Mansa Viewpoint, it is one of the most beautiful places I have ever seen. The fantastic tour

review_text: Lugar unico! De acceso de dificultad media
review_translated_text: Unique place! Medium difficulty access

review_text: Hermoso lugar. Paz  y tranquilidad. La vista increible
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. Peace and tranquility. The incredible view

review_text: Muy lindo lugar con una vista excepcional!! Se accede por un divertido camino en medio de un bosque. Al llegar a un punto a unos 700 metros del ingreso, el camino se divide y se puede ir al Mirador Bahia Mansa o Brava. Tanto el camino, como el entorno y la vista, son excepcionales. El ingreso comparte el primer tramo con el sendero que lleva al Bosque de Arrayanes, si solo se va a los miradores, no se paga la tasa de parques nacionales.
review_translated_text: Very nice place with an exceptional view!! It is accessed by a fun path in the middle of a forest. When you reach a point about 700 meters from the entrance, the path divides and you can go to the Bahia Mansa or Brava Viewpoint. Both the path, the environment and the view are exceptional. The entrance shares the first section with the path that leads to the Arrayanes Forest, if you only go to the viewpoints, you do not pay the national parks fee.

review_text: Hay dos caminos: El inferior, es de 800 metros y es muy facil hacerlo, se ingresa por una tranquera; y el superior que es muy dificil para cualquier edad y estado fisico y se recorre aproximadamente 2 kilometros de subida y con cuidado de no tropezar con las raices de los arboles, pero llegando arriba del cerro, se saca las mejores postales de Bahia Mansa y Brazo Norte. No cobran entrada para llegar.
review_translated_text: There are two paths: The lower one is 800 meters long and is very easy to do, you enter through a gate; and the upper one, which is very difficult for any age and physical condition and is covered approximately 2 kilometers uphill and being careful not to trip over the roots of the trees, but reaching the top of the hill, you get the best postcards of Bahia Mansa and Brazo North. There is no entrance fee to get there.

review_text: Hermosas caminatas para llegar a los dos miradores. Una vez atravesado los 800 metros iniciales, que son los mas empinados, la caminata practicamente no presenta dificultades. El trayecto puede realizarse a pie o en bicicleta. Los senderos estan muy bien senalizados. Las vistas son increibles, el agua transparente con unos colores impresionantes. Muy recomendable!
review_translated_text: Beautiful hikes to reach the two viewpoints. Once you have crossed the initial 800 meters, which are the steepest, the walk presents practically no difficulties. The journey can be done on foot or by bicycle. The trails are very well marked. The views are incredible, the water transparent with impressive colors. Highly recommended!

review_text: Caminata exigente en subida, no es larga pero no es apta para todos los estados fisicos, excelente vista al llegar.
review_translated_text: Demanding hike uphill, it is not long but it is not suitable for all physical states, excellent view upon arrival.

review_text: Muy linda vista, pero mejor el mirador de bahia brava
review_translated_text: Very nice view, but the Bahia Brava viewpoint is better

review_text: Se puede apreciar toda la bahia brava y varios cerros. El acceso a este mirador no tiene costo. El mirador esta muy bien ubicado y la plataforma esta muy bien instalada; aun asi deberian mejorar la cartelera que ya tiene anos y es poco legible.
review_translated_text: You can see the entire Brava Bay and several hills. Access to this viewpoint has no cost. The viewpoint is very well located and the platform is very well installed; Even so, they should improve the billboard, which is already years old and poorly legible.

review_text: Espectacular vista. Pega mas el viento.... Por eso lo d brava.
review_translated_text: Spectacular view. The wind hits harder.... Thats why its so brave.

review_text: Si llueve/nieva vayan con cuidado, me cai unas 7 veces subiendo hasta el miradorxd
review_translated_text: If it rains/snows, be careful, I fell about 7 times going up to the viewpoint

review_text: Hermoso, muy tranquilo y con unas vistas maravillosas!!!
review_translated_text: Beautiful, very quiet and with wonderful views!!!

review_text: Sendero sencillo y corto, ideal para el turismo recreativo. Lo unico malo es que el mirador en si es muy pequeno, no entran muchas personas y los de atras no pueden ver mucho.
review_translated_text: Simple and short trail, ideal for recreational tourism. The only bad thing is that the viewpoint itself is very small, not many people enter and those in the back cant see much.

review_text: Hermoso mirador Se ingresa por el bosque de Arrayanes, el sendero tiene subidas pronunciadas y por tamos escalonadas es un poco pesado pero vale la pena hacerlo El camino hasta los miradores toma una hora y media aproximadamente Luego esta la opcion de seguir todo el recorrido hasta el bosque de Arrayanes que se puede hacer caminando o en bici Para las bici el primer tramo es complejo por las subidas escalonadas... Ir temprano es la mejor opcion para recorrerlo tranquilo y haciendo las paradas que sean necesarias
review_translated_text: Beautiful viewpoint You enter through the Arrayanes forest, the path has steep climbs and stepped terrain, it is a little heavy but it is worth doing The walk to the viewpoints takes approximately an hour and a half. Then there is the option of following the entire route to the Arrayanes forest, which can be done on foot or by bike. For bikes, the first section is complex because of the staggered climbs... Going early is the best option to explore it calmly and making the stops that are necessary.

review_text: Se ingresa por la entrada al PN Los Arrayanes. Es todo en ascenso, ojo xq es agotador. Camino al principio de escalinatas, luego es un sendero en el medio del bosque. Estar atentos a las senales para no pasarse. La visual es muy buena. Deberian cambiar el cartel que te senala lo que ves, porque esta gastado por el sol y lleno de graffitis de gente danina. Mucho viento. Solo hay un relieve rocoso para sentarse un rato.
review_translated_text: It is entered through the entrance to Los Arrayanes NP. Its all on the rise, be careful because it is exhausting. I walk at the beginning of stairs, then it is a path in the middle of the forest. Pay attention to the signs so as not to go too far. The visual is very good. They should change the sign that tells you what you see, because it is worn by the sun and full of graffiti from harmful people. Windy. There is only a rocky relief to sit on for a while.

review_translated_text: It was a 30 minute climb to reach a viewpoint covered by trees. If the trees werent there the view seems beautiful. But we couldnt appreciate it. They charge you like everything else in the south for the entry fee to the park
