Hermoso lugar que no tiene. Que dejar de visitar si van a villa la angostura. Tiene la entrada al bosque de Arrayanes con un sendero para realizarlo caminando y tambien pueden contratar una excursion en barco hacia el mismo bosque pueden ir y volver en el mismo o ir hasta el bosque en barco y volver caminando, experiencia inolvidable.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place that does not have. What to miss if you go to Villa La Angostura. It has the entrance to the Arrayanes forest with a path to walk and you can also hire a boat excursion to the same forest, you can go and return in it or go to the forest by boat and return walking, an unforgettable experience.

review_text: Es un lugar imperdible, vayan sin dudarlo. La paz que se siente de ver ese paisaje, y mas si les toca un dia de sol, con cielo despejado. Sonado    se robo mi corazon con tan solo verlo
review_translated_text: It is an unmissable place, go without hesitation. The peace you feel from seeing that landscape, and even more so if it is a sunny day, with clear skies. Dreamed    he stole my heart just by seeing him

review_text: Es un lugar de en suenos . El dia que fuimos estaba nublado y realmente estaba el agua de un color precioso. Siento que la camara no capta el color de la misma manera que mi propia vista. En persona es mucho mas hermoso
review_translated_text: It is a place of dreams. The day we went it was cloudy and the water was really a beautiful color. I feel like the camera doesnt pick up color the same way my own eyesight does. In person it is much more beautiful

review_text: Beautiful place, one of the postcards that I have in my mind, very quiet, we enjoyed the view from the dock, it was part of the 7 lakes tour. I was surprised by the turquoise green color of the water, it reminded me of Santorini.
Increible lugar playa de piedras finas y el agua calidad cerca de la orilla, una profundidad excelente para estar con familia y pocas molestias de lanchas y botes. Ideal para pasar el dia.
review_translated_text: Incredible beach place with fine stones and quality water near the shore, an excellent depth to be with the family and few disturbances from boats and boats. Ideal to spend the day.

review_text: Excelente playa para descansar. Se encuentra al reparo del viento por lo que es muy tranquila para la tarde y sus aguas son cristalinas.
review_translated_text: Excellent beach to rest. It is sheltered from the wind so it is very calm in the afternoon and its waters are crystal clear.

review_text: El paseo al bosque de arrayanes es precioso, saliendo de la bahia mansa, embarcado dura 45 min y el paseo guiado por el bosque aproximadamente 1 hora. Muy recomendable
review_translated_text: The walk to the myrtle forest is beautiful, leaving the Mansa Bay, the boat ride lasts 45 minutes and the guided walk through the forest takes approximately 1 hour. Highly recommended

review_text: Hermosa playa. Vale la pena visitarla y pasar el dia ahi. Hay bano, muy limpio por cierto. Esta justo la entrada al Parque Nacional Los Arrayanes, pagando entrada podes hacer un trekking de 11k. Podes ir en bote tambien al bosque de los Arrayanes si no podes ir caminando.
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach. It is worth visiting and spending the day there. There is a bathroom, very clean by the way. It is right at the entrance to Los Arrayanes National Park, paying entry you can do an 11k trek. You can also go by boat to the Arrayanes forest if you cannot walk.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, muy agotadora la subida a los miradores y bosques los arrayanes.  Hermosa vista
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, very exhausting the climb to the viewpoints and Arrayanes forests. Beautiful view

review_text: Playa muy linda y tranquila, poco viento, mucho sol, cuenta con zona delimitada y vigilada por guardavidas, alquiler de kayak y otras actividades. Para pasar todo el dia. Estacionamiento ahi cerca o sino a un par de cuadras pero se llega facil.
review_translated_text: Very nice and quiet beach, little wind, lots of sun, has a delimited area supervised by lifeguards, kayak rental and other activities. To spend the whole day. Parking nearby or a couple of blocks away but easy to get to.

review_text: Una playa tranquila, con linda vista. Cuando fuimos no habia mucha gente siendo en febrero y un dia lindo. Hay gente que alquila kayaks y equipo para hacer buceo. Recomiendo alquilar kayak por lo menos una hora para disfrutar un poco mas del lugar y pasear un rato en el agua. La playa es linda para meterse, aunque no lo hice porque el agua estaba fria ese dia
review_translated_text: A quiet beach, with a nice view. When we went there werent many people being in February and it was a nice day. There are people who rent kayaks and diving equipment. I recommend renting a kayak for at least an hour to enjoy the place a little more and walk in the water for a while. The beach is nice to go on, although I didnt do it because the water was cold that day.

review_text: Increible lugar. Fui por la manana para hacer la excursion a Arrayanes en catamaran y volver a pie 12km por el bosque. Quede fascinada
review_translated_text: Incredible place. I went in the morning to take the excursion to Arrayanes by catamaran and return on foot 12km through the forest. I was fascinated

review_text: Hermoso lugar. A unas cuadras esta Bahia Brava y ahi si habia mucho viento. En Bahia mansa es ideal para pasar el dia o estar un buen rato tomando unos mates con un paisaje inigualable
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. A few blocks away is Bahia Brava and there was a lot of wind there. In Bahia Mansa it is ideal to spend the day or have a good time having some mates with an unparalleled landscape

review_text: Para cruzar el lago hasta el Bosque de Arrayanes hay 2 empresas grandes de catamaran, cobran 40.000 pesos argentinos por cruzar ida y vuelta. Tambien esta la opcion de los botes mas chicos, estos cobran 30.000, nosotros optamos por la opcion mas economica y estuvo muy bueno @goarrayanes_turismolacustre. 1 hora de ida, 1 hora en el parque, 1 hora de vuelta. El ticket al parque se compra en bahia mansa antes de zarpar, valor 6.000 aprox.
review_translated_text: To cross the lake to the Arrayanes Forest there are 2 large catamaran companies, they charge 40,000 Argentine pesos to cross round trip. There is also the option of the smaller boats, these charge 30,000, we opted for the cheapest option and it was very good @goarrayanes_turismolacustre. 1 hour there, 1 hour in the park, 1 hour back. The ticket to the park is purchased in Bahia Mansa before setting sail, value 6,000 approx.

review_text: Exelente lugar para acampar en el camping Dona Arsilla. Don jorge Muy Buena persona Buena Atencion
review_translated_text: Excellent place to camp at the Dona Arsilla campsite. Don Jorge Very good person Good attention

review_text: Villa la angostura es todo lo que esta bien en el mundo  . Tanto bahia mansa como bahia brava son hermosas  prefiero mansa los dias que fuimos habia menos gente en esta   las vistas increibles   La Paz Punto en contra :no hay sombra, nosotros buscamos un ratito debajo del puente  . Sino tenes que irte del lado de arrayanes digamos. El agua bastante fria   pero bueno te adaptas   . Estaria bueno que haya servicios mas cerca Tenes banos en el inicio al sendero del bosque de arrayanes. Impecables. 150 metros aprox Y licuados, etc minimo a 200 metros. Cerca el muelle de donde salen catamaranes para excursiones. Kayak para alquilar.
review_translated_text: Villa la Angostura is everything that is good in the world  . Both Bahia Mansa and Bahia Brava are beautiful  I prefer Mansa. The days we went there were less people in this one  the incredible views  La Paz Point against: there is no shade, we look under the bridge for a little while  . Otherwise you have to go to the Arrayanes side, lets say. The water is quite cold  but good tea you can adapt   . It would be nice if there were services closer You have bathrooms at the beginning of the myrtle forest trail. Impeccable. 150 meters approx And smoothies, etc. at least 200 meters away. Near the dock where catamarans leave for excursions. Kayak for rent.

review_text: One of the beaches that you do or do have to visit if you go to Villa La Angostura. Bahia Mansa is smoother, and La Brava has more wind, both are beautiful and very close to each other. I recommend spending the day if its summer or the afternoon if its autumn now (because it gets a little cooler) to have some mates with those beautiful views.
Increible lugar. La playa es un 10 y super tranquila.
review_translated_text: Incredible place. The beach is a 10 and super quiet.

review_text: Beautiful place; to spend the time; to take a lake excursion or do some activity like kayaking. Not to mention if you want to take photos or simply enjoy the view and nature. Dreamed of!!
Que hermoso lugar! Fuimos para tomar el catamaran al bosque los arrayanes. Un lugar de cuento de hadas, precioso
review_translated_text: What a beautiful place! We went to take the catamaran to the Arrayanes forest. A fairy tale place, beautiful

review_text: Lugar maravilloso, con un paisaje y tranquilidad unica
review_translated_text: Wonderful place, with a unique landscape and tranquility

review_text: Hermoso rinconcito de la villa,para conectar con el lago y las montanas    . De este lado de la Bahia siempre hay menos viento y es un punto imperdible!
review_translated_text: Beautiful little corner of the villa, to connect with the lake and the mountains    . On this side of the Bay there is always less wind and it is a must-see spot!

review_text: Magical place, you can breathe a lot of peace and tranquility, you can appreciate the smallness of the human being in the face of the immensity of nature, which is simply wonderful. Ideal for walking, drinking mate and relaxing. I was able to meet it in the fall season and with a day of little wind and ideal temperature so it was a spectacle.
Beautiful place, super quiet and not so crowded. I recommend renting half an hour of kayaking, the experience is great, the water is super crystal clear and the landscapes are incredible.
Hermoso hermoso hermoso hermoso. Vale recontra la pena ir. Imperdible. Banos cerca, lugar donde dejar el auto, kiosquito, bosques. Kayak impresionannnte.
review_translated_text: Beautiful beautiful beautiful beautiful. It is worth going again. Safety pin. Bathrooms nearby, place to leave the car, kiosk, forests. Impressive kayak.

review_text: Beautiful place. We went on a weekday and there werent many people. The ice water.

La vista y el rio es espectacular. Para mi el agua muy helada, pero he visto a personas banarse. Hicimos kayak y nos cobraron 4000 pesos (2p x 1h) luego preguntamos y no dijeron que nos vieron la cara. Parece que el precio es menos. Mas alla de esos es fantastico
review_translated_text: The view and the river are spectacular. For me the water is very cold, but I have seen people bathe. We kayaked and they charged us 4000 pesos (2p x 1h) then we asked and they didnt say they saw our faces. It seems that the price is less. Beyond those its fantastic

review_text: Hermoso lugar. Itsmo. Costado ingreso parque nacional Arrayanes y paseos en lancha. Trecking de 11 kms. 2 lagos en su
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. Isthmus. Next to Arrayanes National Park entrance and boat rides. 11 km trekking. 2 lakes in your

review_text: Es precioso el lugar, el agua, la playa, hay banos lo que es el ingreso al bosque de arrayanes
review_translated_text: The place is beautiful, the water, the beach, there are bathrooms which is the entrance to the myrtle forest

review_text: La villa entera es hermosa. Pero la bahia es un sueno
review_translated_text: The entire villa is beautiful. But the bay is a dream

review_text: Es un lugar bellisimo y tranquilo, nosotros fuimos  empezando la segunda quincena de febrero, por lo que no habia mucha gente. No vimos letreros que digan que no se permiten perros, de echo muchas familias paseaban con ellos con y sin correa. Es ideal para la familia porque tiene un par de.metros donde la profundidad del agua es pareja, por lo que ninos y adultos pueden banarse. Ademas cuenta con kayak ($3000 la hora) , remo, bici acuatica ( $3000 la hora), botes, lanchas para disfrutar aun mas.
review_translated_text: It is a beautiful and quiet place, we went starting the second half of February, so there were not many people. We did not see signs saying that dogs are not allowed, in fact many families walked with them on and off leash. It is ideal for the family because it has a couple of meters where the depth of the water is even, so children and adults can bathe. It also has kayak ($3000 per hour), rowing, water bike ($3000 per hour), boats, motorboats to enjoy even more.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar, el agua casi igual de fria que en los pozones del bolson jajaja pero bueno hermosa playa.
review_translated_text: Very nice place, the water almost as cold as in the pools of Bolson hahaha but hey, beautiful beach.

review_text: Una de las playas que mas me gusto de Villa La Angostura, por su color, la vista y por sobre todo el hecho de que la misma este resguardada, que hace que no haya tanto viento y su laguna sea mansa como su nombre lo indica. Ideal para andar en Kayak y disfrutar de un dia de playa
review_translated_text: One of the beaches that I liked the most in Villa La Angostura, for its color, the view and above all the fact that it is sheltered, which means that there is not as much wind and its lagoon is calm as its name indicates. Ideal for kayaking and enjoying a day at the beach

review_text: Siempre es bueno hacer el recorrido para llegar a los miradores de las dos Bahias! Dos pajaros nos regalaron una hermosa danza mientras admirabamos el paisaje! Gracias Neuquen por ser tan bello!
review_translated_text: It is always good to take the route to reach the viewpoints of the two Bays! Two birds gave us a beautiful dance while we admired the landscape! Thank you Neuquen for being so beautiful!

review_text: Lugar muy hermoso y parada obligatoria si se va a villa la angostura. Al alejarse un poco de la entrada se puede ir a un costado mucho mas tranquilo y con mucha calma. Camine hasta un muelle muy lindo donde se podia visualizar toda la costa e islas perfectamente.
review_translated_text: Very beautiful place and obligatory stop if you go to Villa La Angostura. By moving a little further away from the entrance you can go to a much quieter and calmer side. I walked to a very nice pier where you could see the entire coast and islands perfectly.

review_text: Me toco visitar este lugar en un dia de lluvia y viento. Igualmente es increible el paisaje.  Tengo que volver para poder disfrutarlo con sol.  Es una cuenta pendiente.
review_translated_text: I had to visit this place on a rainy and windy day. The landscape is also incredible. I have to go back to be able to enjoy it with the sun. It is a pending account.

review_text: Hermoso lugar muy tranquilo
review_translated_text: Beautiful very quiet place

review_text: Hermosa bahia para caminar dentro de un bosque con salida al lago en distintas playas publicas. Tiene cerca el sendero Rio Bonito, recomiendo hacerlo
review_translated_text: Beautiful bay to walk within a forest with access to the lake on different public beaches. The Rio Bonito trail is close by, I recommend doing it

review_text: Lugar impresionante. El agua un dia soleado parece lo mejor del caribe. No hay viento. Si hay bastante gente. Ideal para pasar un lindo dia de playa con vistas espectaculares.
review_translated_text: Stunning place. The water on a sunny day seems like the best thing about the Caribbean. No wind. Yes there are quite a few people. Ideal for spending a nice day at the beach with spectacular views.

review_text: El lugar es muy bonito, en si todo Villa La Angostura es bonito. Recomendable reservar los paseos en barco 1 dia antes porque se llenan. Luego en la playa hay paseos en kayak y unas balsas a pedal. Hay parqueo y bano comodos y tambien restaurantes.
review_translated_text: The place is very beautiful, everything in Villa La Angostura is beautiful. It is advisable to book the boat trips 1 day in advance because they fill up. Then on the beach there are kayak rides and some pedal rafts. There is comfortable parking and bathrooms and also restaurants.

review_text: Un lugar en el mundo, podes quedarte horas contemplado esos colores en ese paisaje que emociona tanto. Que hermosa es nuestra Patagonia.
review_translated_text: A place in the world, you can stay for hours contemplating those colors in that landscape that excites you so much. How beautiful is our Patagonia.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, visita obligatoria si se va a Villa La Angostura. La playa tiene secciones con arena fina y otras con bastantes piedras. Fuimos a los dos miradores, la subida es de aproximadamente un kilometro. Recomiendo llevar unas buenas zapatillas porque la tierra esta muy suelta en algunos tramos del sendero y te podes resbalar. Espectacular la vista de ambos miradores. Se puede hacer tambien un sendero de 11 km hasta el bosque de arrayanes.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, mandatory visit if you go to Villa La Angostura. The beach has sections with fine sand and others with quite a few stones. We went to the two viewpoints, the climb is approximately one kilometer. I recommend wearing good shoes because the ground is very loose in some sections of the trail and you can slip. Spectacular views from both viewpoints. You can also take an 11 km trail to the myrtle forest.

review_text: Espectacular vista y lugar. El mirador es solo un punto dentro del bosque de arrayanes el cual se lleva el premio desde el puerto de VLA tenes un trayecto de 11 km ida y 11 km de vuelta (dejo una foto con el mapa). Pero el mirador esta casi al inicio. Se puede hacer en bici y creo que mejora la experiencia 100 veces, aunque se necesita un poco de estado fisico y una bici mtb. Tambien se puede realizar ida o vuelta(o ambas) en catamaran pero sale un poco caro.
review_translated_text: Spectacular view and place. The viewpoint is just a point within the myrtle forest which takes the prize from the VLA port, you have a journey of 11 km one way and 11 km back (I leave a photo with the map). But the viewpoint is almost at the beginning. It can be done by bike and I think it improves the experience 100 times, although you need a bit of physical fitness and an MTB bike. You can also go or return (or both) by catamaran but it is a little expensive.

review_text: Hermosa Bahia, agua serena y apenas unos grados menos fria que otros destinos del sur. Ideal para poder apreciar la transparencia y la calma del agua,  debe ser parada obligada de aqui,ademas de estar conectada a bahia brava y bosque de arrayanes.
review_translated_text: Beautiful Bay, serene water and just a few degrees less cold than other destinations in the south. Ideal to appreciate the transparency and calm of the water, it should be a mandatory stop here, in addition to being connected to Bahia Brava and myrtle forest.

review_text: Espectacular espacio donde el color y la belleza se apoderan del espacio. Aqui pueden tomarte tu tiempo para relajar tu mente sentarte en la playita y disfrutar de la Natura en su esplendor.
review_translated_text: Spectacular space where color and beauty take over the space. Here you can take your time to relax your mind, sit on the beach and enjoy nature in its splendor.

review_text: Hermoso lugar!!!! Imperdible para ir a visitar. Hay varios lugares muy pintorescos para tomar algo, merendar o comer.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!!!! Not to be missed to visit. There are several very picturesque places to have a drink, snack or eat.

review_text: Una playa hermosa sobre el itsmo de la peninsula Quetrihue y el acceso al parque nacional arrayanes. Suele ser complicado encontrar lugar para estacionar  por lo que es recomendable ir caminando o en bicicleta
review_translated_text: A beautiful beach on the isthmus of the Quetrihue peninsula and access to the Arrayanes National Park. It is usually difficult to find a parking space, so it is advisable to walk or bike.

review_text: Hermoso lugar para relajarse luego de una larga caminata por el bosque de Arrayanes. Hay algunos restaurantes cerca y se puede banar en las playas!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to relax after a long walk through the Arrayanes forest. There are some restaurants nearby and you can swim on the beaches!

review_text: Bello lugar realmente entre bahia mansa y bahia brava, 50mts de distancia y un cambio de energia en las aguas muy notable.
review_translated_text: Really beautiful place between Bahia Mansa and Bahia Brava, 50 meters away and a very notable change of energy in the waters.

review_text: Un lugar unico, hermoso.
review_translated_text: A unique, beautiful place.

review_text: DIA ALUCINANTE. Caminamos desde el centro, pasando por la Capilla Ntra. Sra. de Asuncion, de alli bajamos a la Bahia Mansa previa circunvalacion a la Mansion El Messidor, nos hidratamos en el Restaurante. del Puerto, con una refrescante limonada con jengibre y menta, de alli nos dirigimos a la entrada del PN Arrayanes y subimos hasta el Mirador del Brazo Norte, al bajar sin ganas de esperar los 50 al bus que nos llevaria de nuevo al centro, caminamos de regreso, 15 K que valieron mucho la pena. 70 mi Sra. 85 yo.
review_translated_text: AMAZING DAY. We walked from the center, passing by the Nuestra Senora de Asuncion Chapel, from there we went down to Mansa Bay after circumambulating the El Messidor Mansion, we hydrated at the Restaurant. del Puerto, with a refreshing lemonade with ginger and mint, from there we went to the entrance of the Arrayanes National Park and went up to the Mirador del Brazo Norte, when we went down without wanting to wait the 50 for the bus that would take us back to the center, We walked back, 15K which was very worth it. 70 my Mrs. 85 me.

review_text: Se encuentra en el brazo derecho de villa la angostura, bella vista al lago y al bosque de arrayanes, donde se puede ingresar de dia para caminata. Desde esta bahia salen embarcaciones y excursiones.
review_translated_text: It is located on the right arm of Villa La Angostura, with a beautiful view of the lake and the myrtle forest, where you can enter during the day for a walk. Boats and excursions leave from this bay.

review_text: Hermoso lugar! Perfecto para un paseo y tomar fotos. Con banos, cafes y paseo de artesanos muy cerca.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place! Perfect for a walk and taking photos. With bathrooms, cafes and a walk of artisans very close.

review_text: Uno de los mejores lugares de Puerto Manzano sin dudas. Muy bello
review_translated_text: One of the best places in Puerto Manzano without a doubt. Very beautiful

review_text: Hermoso lugar, para llegar al mirador son aproximadamente 1.2km , super recomendado
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, to get to the viewpoint it is approximately 1.2km, highly recommended

review_text: Hermoso lugar
review_translated_text: Beautiful place

review_text: Si vas a realizar la caminata a bosques de arayanes llevar ropa comoda,agua y los desechos de comida o fruta no dejarlos en el lugar ya que es una reserva ( y habla bien de usted) importante el agua del lago no es potable. Y la caminata tiene una duracion de 2hs.
review_translated_text: If you are going to make the hike to the arayanes forests, bring comfortable clothing, water, and food or fruit waste, do not leave them in the place since it is an important reserve (and this speaks well of you), the water in the lake is not drinkable. And the walk lasts 2 hours.

review_text: Si hay lugar mas precioso,bello, inmaculado , con mucha paz y que no te lo podes perder si venis a Villa Angostura son sus 2 playas la Mansa y la brava!!! NO TE LO PODES PERDER!!! ARGENTINA TIENE LOS MEJORES PAISAJES DESDE EL NORTE AL SUR Y DE ESTE A OSTE ......LO MAS ....
review_translated_text: If there is a more precious, beautiful, immaculate place, with a lot of peace and that you cannot miss if you come to Villa Angostura, it is its 2 beaches, La Mansa and La Brava!!! YOU CAN NOT MISS IT!!! ARGENTINA HAS THE BEST LANDSCAPES FROM THE NORTH TO THE SOUTH AND FROM EAST TO WEST......THE MOST....

review_text: Es una experiencia unica, como el bosque, su principal atractivo es eso, un bosque unico en el mundo. La guia te explica y ensena todo, muy profesional. Tiene un valor de 5.500 por persona. Y ademas 800 para entrar al parque.. un poco caro. La casita del te para nada recomendable. No vale la pena, 1 porcion de torta 900 pesos y cada cafe de maquina en vasitos descartables 400, no lo vale. Lo demas todo excelente y super recomendable.
review_translated_text: It is a unique experience, like the forest, its main attraction is that, a unique forest in the world. The guide explains and teaches you everything, very professional. It has a value of 5,500 per person. And also 800 to enter the park... a little expensive. The tea house is not recommended at all. Its not worth it, 1 slice of cake is 900 pesos and each machine coffee in disposable cups is 400, its not worth it. The rest is all excellent and highly recommended.

review_text: Una breve pero empinada caminata desde la entrada del Parque Arrayanes te lleva hasta este mirador. Vale la pena. La vista de Bahia Mansa es una belleza. No dejes de subir. A la entrada del Parque banos bastante limpios.
review_translated_text: A short but steep walk from the entrance to Parque Arrayanes takes you to this viewpoint. Its worth it. The view of Bahia Mansa is beautiful. Dont stop climbing. At the entrance to the Park, bathrooms are quite clean.

review_text: Un lugar maravilloso para conectar con la naturaleza.
review_translated_text: A wonderful place to connect with nature.

review_text: It is impossible not to cry when you reach the chasm. The trail is long but it is worth it. Seeing so much of Gods creation all together. I cried all over.    Villa LANGOSTURA looks wonderful from here
Todos los lugares que visite en mi excursion desde San Martin de los Andes, haciendo siete lagos, arrayanes y Villa Langostura son dignos de visitar .Sus paisajes son de ensuenos.
review_translated_text: All the places I visited on my excursion from San Martin de los Andes, making seven lakes, myrtle trees and Villa Langostura, are worth visiting. Their landscapes are dreamlike.

review_text: Una vez por ano la visito, y nunca me deja de sorprender  tanta belleza. Esta vez nos sorprendio la nieve , despues de haber disfrutado la variedad de colores en su vegetacion. Una maravilla!!!!!
review_translated_text: I visit it once a year, and it never ceases to amaze me with its beauty. This time we were surprised by the snow, after having enjoyed the variety of colors in its vegetation. A marvel!!!!!

review_text: Hermosa playa, tranquila y pacifica para descanso. Es interesante tambien para probar Kayak si es tu primera vez. O simplemente comer algo, o descansar con el lago de fondo. Mas que recomendable.
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach, quiet and peaceful for rest. It is also interesting to try Kayak if it is your first time. Or just eat something, or rest with the lake in the background. More than recommended.

review_text: Hermoso lugar para descansar la mente. Cuando esta despejado, el sol se ve todo el dia y se siente el calorcito a full. El agua es muuuy fria, creeme y aunquesea pleno verano; es por eso que no mucha gente se mete y por lo general poca gente frecuenta (se pasa a la bajada del lado opuesto).  Se puede pasar todo el dia y hay un barrio cerca por si no llevan comida.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to rest your mind. When it is clear, the sun is visible all day and you feel the warmth in full. The water is very cold, believe me and even if it is the middle of summer; That is why not many people get involved and generally few people frequent it (they go to the descent on the opposite side). You can spend the whole day and there is a neighborhood nearby in case they dont bring food.

review_text: Hermoso rincon de Villa la Angostura. Lo visitamos este finde largo de noviembre 2021 y estaba muy tranquilo. En verano se debe llenar pero no deja de ser una visita obligatoria. El lago con su degrade de colores, un pequeno sendero, el muelle y la arenita hacen un lugar perfecto.
review_translated_text: Beautiful corner of Villa la Angostura. We visited it this long weekend in November 2021 and it was very quiet. In summer it must be full but it is still a mandatory visit. The lake with its gradient of colors, a small path, the pier and the sand make a perfect place.

review_text: Increible lugar para pasar el dia! Dos bahias hermosas para meterte al agua en verano, apreciar los paisajes y relajar. Algo muy positivo es que tiene un area de servicios muy cerca con bares, restaurantes y kiosco. Esta re cerca del centro de Villa y si vas con el auto tenes una playa de estacionamiento gratuita donde tambien hay banos publicos.
review_translated_text: Amazing place to spend the day! Two beautiful bays to get into the water in summer, appreciate the landscapes and relax. Something very positive is that it has a service area very close with bars, restaurants and a kiosk. It is close to the center of Villa and if you go by car you have a free parking lot where there are also public bathrooms.

review_text: Impresionante, bellisimos  paisajes ,para disfrutar y admirar.
review_translated_text: Impressive, beautiful landscapes, to enjoy and admire.

review_text: Camino al bosque de los Arrayanes. Hermoso lugar para visitar! Fui hasta los miradores. Para llegar hay que ir cuesta arriba alrededor de un kilometro, pero vale la pena. Dato: hasta alli no te cobran entrada.
review_translated_text: Road to the Arrayanes forest. Beautiful place to visit! I went to the viewpoints. To get there you have to go uphill for about a kilometer, but it is worth it. Fact: they dont charge you an entrance fee until there.

review_text: The beach has a very nice view! From here the excursion to the Arrayanes Forest departs by catamaran. The walk was very beautiful and the guide was a genius, she explained to us in great detail throughout the entire excursion.

Uno de los lugares mas lindo que he conocida. Pude conocer este lugar una manana muy temprano donde habia un poco de neblina, el agua era como un espejo y el amanecer hizo que paisaje fuera increible. El agua tiene un color genial. Debe ser uno de los lugares mas bonitos de la Argentina.
review_translated_text: One of the most beautiful places I have ever known. I was able to see this place very early one morning where there was a little fog, the water was like a mirror and the sunrise made the landscape incredible. The water has a great color. It must be one of the most beautiful places in Argentina.

review_text: A 3km del centro de la villa se encuentra esta bahia, ideal para pasar un rato viendo el imponente paisaje. Se puede hacer un paseo en catamaran que salen desde ahi al Parque Nacional Arrayanes.
review_translated_text: 3km from the center of the town is this bay, ideal for spending some time watching the impressive landscape. You can take a catamaran ride that departs from there to the Arrayanes National Park.

review_text: Mi opinion es en base a lo que pude hacer. El lugar es muy tranquilo, hay un sector de playa habilitado, y tambien se puede alquilar distintos elementos como canoas, botes etc para pasar un rato remando en el lago. La vista panoramica es muy linda, el agua se torna turquesa a medida que pasa el dia, por lo que note se forma de esta manera por los minerales que estan en la costa que al sumergirse en el agua produce un efecto de turquesa. Muy lindo. En general el agua no es muy fria, ideal para sobrellevar un dia pesado, ya que los dias que estuve el clima promediaba los 30 grados. En conclusion, recomiendo el lugar, hay lugares apartados de las personas, y hay lugares exclusivamente para meterse al agua.
review_translated_text: My opinion is based on what I was able to do. The place is very quiet, there is a beach section enabled, and you can also rent different items such as canoes, boats, etc. to spend some time paddling on the lake. The panoramic view is very beautiful, the water turns turquoise as the day goes by, so note that it is formed this way by the minerals that are on the coast that when immersed in the water produces a turquoise effect. Very pretty. In general, the water is not very cold, ideal for getting through a hard day, since the days I was there the weather averaged 30 degrees. In conclusion, I recommend the place, there are places away from people, and there are places exclusively for getting into the water.

review_text: Lugar bellisimo  a metros de las 2 playas, se ingresa por el sendero que te lleva al bosque de arrayanes
review_translated_text: Beautiful place   meters from the 2 beaches, you enter through the path that takes you to the myrtle forest

review_text: La playa es MUY HERMOSA, tiene unos colores turquesas muy lindos. Mucha paz, no es tan concurrida. Tiene bancos para sentarse. Se puede llegar en auto y tiene un recorrido por un bosque de arrayanes para hacer caminando.
review_translated_text: The beach is VERY BEAUTIFUL, it has very pretty turquoise colors. A lot of peace, its not that busy. It has benches to sit on. It can be reached by car and has a tour through a myrtle forest to do on foot.

review_text: Hermosa vista, entramos al bosque de arrayanes y vimos la inmensidad de esta bahia desde uno de sus miradores. Una vez que finalizamos el recorrido, frenamos en la bahia a tomar mates y disfrutar viendo el lago. Una parada obligatoria si estan por ahi. Su color de agua es unico y es muy bello
review_translated_text: Beautiful view, we entered the myrtle forest and saw the immensity of this bay from one of its viewpoints. Once we finished the tour, we stopped at the bay to drink mates and enjoy watching the lake. A mandatory stop if you are there. Its water color is unique and very beautiful.

review_text: Hermoso mirador, con playas super tranquilas ideal para pasar un rato tomando algo y mirando semejante horizonte. De ahi salen los catamaran al bosque de arrayanes
review_translated_text: Beautiful viewpoint, with super quiet beaches, ideal for spending some time having a drink and looking at such a horizon. From there the catamarans leave for the myrtle forest.

review_text: Hermosa vista luego de una caminata de 30 minutos en subida. La hice con mi hijo de 6 anos y se canso un poco, pero vale la pena el esfuerzo.
review_translated_text: Beautiful view after a 30-minute walk uphill. I did it with my 6 year old son and he got a little tired, but its worth the effort.

review_text: Una preciosura, el agua en lugares es turquesa y en otros es azul, muy muy bella, la mejor vista, desde los miradores del Parque Nacional Los Arrayanes
review_translated_text: A beauty, the water in places is turquoise and in others it is blue, very very beautiful, the best view, from the viewpoints of the Los Arrayanes National Park

review_text: Muy hermoso.
review_translated_text: Very beautiful.

review_text: Just look at the pictures and the information post. The view is amazing and you can get here after walking 1-1/2 km into the Los Arrayanes National Park in the free path. Please consider that in the first few kilometers the road has stairs and the inclination could be challenging for elderlies.

Otro hermoso lugar, para visitar cuando uno llega a Villa La Angostura. Es un playa donde hay varios lugares para comer (no son muy baratos) pero se come muy bien. Si vas en auto podes llevar tu comida y almorzar o merendar sobre la playa con una vista increible del lago Nahuel Huapi.
review_translated_text: Another beautiful place to visit when one arrives at Villa La Angostura. It is a beach where there are several places to eat (they are not very cheap) but the food is very good. If you go by car you can bring your food and have lunch or a snack on the beach with an incredible view of Lake Nahuel Huapi.

review_text: Hermosa playita antes del bosque de los arrayanes
review_translated_text: Beautiful little beach before the myrtle forest

review_text: Hermoso lugar, un paraje excelente para estar en la playa tomar mate con churros y andar en kayak
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, an excellent place to be on the beach, drink mate with churros and go kayaking

review_text: Hermoso lugar para visitar y pasar unas horas. El agua es fria pero sus colores son hermosos. Hay banos y locales cerca.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to visit and spend a few hours. The water is cold but its colors are beautiful. There are bathrooms and shops nearby.

review_text: You can go by catamaran to the Arrayanes Forest, but it is cheaper to go by boat. They only leave in the morning, and the catamaran leaves until 3:00 p.m. Another option is to ride a pedal boat, which is cheap and you can choose half an hour or more. There are no tables or chairs to sit on the beach. The water is crystal clear and green. Very beautiful.
Lindo sendero con maravillosas vistas de la bahia. Bien senalizado y de facil acceso. Con explicaciones para observar fauna y vegetacion.
review_translated_text: Nice trail with wonderful views of the bay. Well signposted and easy to access. With explanations to observe fauna and vegetation.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, llevar kayak si tenes , ideal para ir a tomar unos mates!!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, bring a kayak if you have one, ideal to go and have some mates!!

review_text: Beautiful place. Totally paradisiacal waters and a spectacular landscape. It is worth going almost any time of year, but I highly recommend going in the summer to get the most out of it, maybe even kayaking.
El agua mas linda que vi en mi estadia fue la de Bahia Mansa. De todos modos hay que saber que el agua es muy fria, pero el paisaje lo hace valer totalmente
review_translated_text: The most beautiful water I saw during my stay was that of Bahia Mansa. In any case, you have to know that the water is very cold, but the landscape makes it totally worth it.

review_text: Es un lugar maravilloso con paisajes magnificos con salida hacia el parque los arrayanes que su precio varia ida y vuelta en bote por 800-900 pesos argentinos aproximadamente
review_translated_text: It is a wonderful place with magnificent landscapes with departure to Los Arrayanes Park whose price varies round trip by boat for approximately 800-900 Argentine pesos

review_text: Bellisimo lugar, hay lugares para comer, artesanos, Kayak, playita, estacionamiento... visita obligada cuando vas a Villa La Angostura.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, there are places to eat, artisans, Kayak, beach, parking... a must-see when you go to Villa La Angostura.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar en Villa la Angostura
review_translated_text: Very nice place in Villa la Angostura

review_text: Es un lugar hermoso! Asi sea cerca de la entrada al parque nacional Los Arrayanes donde el agua junto al sol se forma ese verde esmeralda tan caracteristico o ir bordeando el lago ya que la bahia es grande para encontrar tu lugar tranquilo en la sombra! PD: subir al mirador del parque nacional y capturarlo desde arriba, alucinante!
review_translated_text: It is a beautiful place! Whether it is near the entrance to the Los Arrayanes National Park where the water next to the sun forms that characteristic emerald green or go along the lake since the bay is large to find your quiet place in the shade! PS: go up to the national park viewpoint and capture it from above, amazing!

review_text: Impactante lugar, hermoso para disfrutar en pareja o con la familia, es la tercera vez que venimos y la verdad siempre te sorprende la vista , el aire fresco y la amabilidad de las personas. Altamente recomendable.
review_translated_text: Stunning place, beautiful to enjoy as a couple or with the family, it is the third time we come and the truth is that you are always surprised by the view, the fresh air and the kindness of the people. Highly recommended.

review_text: Un lugar para disfrutar del paisaje y su paz
review_translated_text: A place to enjoy the landscape and its peace

review_text: Una belleza...se respira paz, excelente lugar para descansar
review_translated_text: A beauty...you breathe peace, excellent place to rest

review_text: Lugar super tranquilo, ideal para ir en familia. Linda el agua, lugar limpio y prolijo. En el entorno hay variados servicios. El paisaje y la tranquilidad inigualables. Muy recomendable
review_translated_text: Super quiet place, ideal to go with the family. Beautiful water, clean and neat place. There are various services in the environment. The unmatched landscape and tranquility. Highly recommended

review_text: Hermoso, hicimos kayak y caminamos por la playita, que cosa tan linda y el agua estaba espectacular. Me encanto! No dejen de ir tambien se puede conocer el bosque de arrayanes.
review_translated_text: Beautiful, we kayaked and walked along the beach, what a beautiful thing and the water was spectacular. I loved! Dont forget to go, you can also see the myrtle forest.

review_text: Muy linda playa. Se puede ir a pie 12km desde alli al bosque de arrayanes. Una belleza
review_translated_text: Very nice beach. You can walk 12km from there to the myrtle forest. A beauty

review_text: El lago Hermoso es una visita obligada para quien quiera recorrer los 7 lagos, los dias sin vientos se puede ver la transparecia de sus aguas y es un espejo de las montanas que lo rodean
review_translated_text: Lake Hermoso is a must-see for anyone who wants to explore the 7 lakes. On windless days you can see the transparency of its waters and it is a mirror of the mountains that surround it.

review_text: Si estas en Villa la Angostura no te pierdas de ver los dos miradores partiendo de la entrada al istmo de Quetrihuel, tenes bano a la entrada y juegos para ninos, eso si el ascenso los primeros metros es pesado pero vale la pena.
review_translated_text: If you are in Villa la Angostura dont miss seeing the two viewpoints starting from the entrance to the Quetrihuel isthmus, you have a bathroom at the entrance and games for children, although the climb the first few meters is hard but it is worth it.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar, un paisaje unico.
review_translated_text: Very nice place, a unique landscape.

review_text: Sin dudas un lugar que vale la pena visitar si van a Villa la Angostura! El color del agua es hermoso y la playa es de arena por lo que es super comoda. En el lugar hay sanitarios. Sin dudas un 10
review_translated_text: Without a doubt a place worth visiting if you go to Villa la Angostura! The color of the water is beautiful and the beach is sandy so it is super comfortable. There are toilets on site. Without a doubt a 10

review_text: Un lugar sonado,caminata en sendero plano,sin complicacion, arbolado, con un rio turqueza que se destacaba por varios miradores,para fotos postales,maravilloso,no se lo pierdan,
review_translated_text: A dream place, a walk on a flat path, without complications, wooded, with a turquoise river that stood out for several viewpoints, for postcard photos, wonderful, dont miss it,

review_text: Hermoso lugar de un lado tenes bahia mansa y del otro bahia brava. Lo unico que hace la diferencia son las montanas. De un lado repara el viento y del otro no, por eso es mas movido
review_translated_text: Beautiful place on one side you have Bahia Mansa and on the other Bahia Brava. The only thing that makes a difference are the mountains. On one side the wind heals and on the other it doesnt, thats why its more moving.

review_text: Todo fue una experiencia maravillosa,  desde que subimos al catamaran hasta el bosque de Arrayanes!!! Es como estar dentro de un libro de cuentos
review_translated_text: Everything was a wonderful experience, from the moment we boarded the catamaran to the Arrayanes forest!!! Its like being inside a storybook

review_text: Hermoso lugar recomendable para visitar y disfrutar a pleno de la belleza  mas aun en verano
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, recommended to visit and fully enjoy the beauty, even more so in summer.

review_text: Es hermoso y tranquilo. Camino al bosque de arrayanes, hay una playa pequena con guardavidas.  El paisaje es unico.  Hay una escuela de buceo super recomendable para primerizos y buzos certificados.
review_translated_text: It is beautiful and peaceful. On the way to the myrtle forest, there is a small beach with lifeguards. The landscape is unique. There is a highly recommended diving school for first-timers and certified divers.

review_text: Lugar maravilloso. Es imposible dejar plasmado en fotos lo sonado de este lugar! Recorrimos la playa y comimos en un restaurante llamado Porto Seguro, al dia de hoy es nuevo, no tiene lugar en Google maps para resenas, por eso lo dejo asentado. Sin dudas (y sin exagerar) el mejor lugar donde hemos comido. Ravioles de trucha y salmon Y de postre la especialidad de la casa: mousse de chocolate con gajos de frutilla.
review_translated_text: Amazing place. It is impossible to capture in photos the dream of this place! We walked the beach and ate at a restaurant called Porto Seguro, as of today it is new, it has no place on Google maps for reviews, thats why I leave it stated. Without a doubt (and without exaggeration) the best place we have eaten. Trout and salmon ravioli And for dessert, the house specialty: chocolate mousse with strawberry segments.

review_text: Hermosoo , hay un sendero que costea el rio bonito , muy lindo
review_translated_text: Beautiful, there is a path that runs along the beautiful river, very nice

review_text: Hermoso un lugar encantador te quedas enamorado de tanta belleza si pudiera ir todos los dias es el lugar perfecto para descansar o relajarse.
review_translated_text: Beautiful, a charming place, you will fall in love with so much beauty. If you could go every day, it is the perfect place to rest or relax.

review_text: El esfuerzo vale la pena. Es un lugar que no se puede dejar de visitar. La vista es espectacular. Un regalo para los sentidos. El paisaje es magnifico. Altamente recomendable. Y por supuesto, seguir luego hasta el bosque de Arrayanes. No se pierdan por ningun motivo el mirador de la Bahia Brava.
review_translated_text: The effort is worth it. It is a place that cannot be missed. The view is spectacular. A gift for the senses. The landscape is magnificent. Highly recommended. And of course, continue then to the Arrayanes forest. Dont miss the Bahia Brava viewpoint for any reason.

review_text: Un lugar increible. Un sendero de 11 km de dificultad media por tramos pero en gran parte en sencillo. Muy lindos paisajes
review_translated_text: An incredible place. An 11 km trail of medium difficulty in sections but largely easy. Very nice landscapes

review_text: Una playa muy linda y limpia a minutos de Villa la Angostura, totalmente recomendado
review_translated_text: A very nice and clean beach minutes from Villa la Angostura, totally recommended

review_text: Espectacular , una playa para pasar todo el dia tranquilo. Mucho silencio y sol. El paisaje es imponemte y hay una gran cantidad de servicios a pocos metros.
review_translated_text: Spectacular, a beach to spend the whole day peacefully. Lots of silence and sun. The landscape is imposing and there are a large number of services just a few meters away.

review_text: Preciosa bahia, con mucho menos viento que la Bahia Brava y con mucha mas sombra. Muy buena para hacer kayak!! 12000 la hora de kayak doble en enero 2024.
review_translated_text: Beautiful bay, with much less wind than Bahia Brava and with much more shade. Very good for kayaking!! 12,000 per hour of double kayaking in January 2024.

review_text: La mejor playa de todas, una tranquilidad y paz tremenda, el agua es de lo mejor. Una vista inigualable. El bano queda a unas 4 cuadrqs que es el bano publico. Playa ambiente y agua de 10.
review_translated_text: The best beach of all, tremendous tranquility and peace, the water is the best. An unmatched view. The bathroom is about 4 blocks away, which is the public bathroom. Beach environment and water 10.

review_text: Hermoso lugar para pasar el dia, lastimas las abejas que no te dejan en paz
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to spend the day, it hurts the bees that wont leave you alone

review_text: Precioso lugar para disfrutar de un descanso en familia ,con amigos o en soledad, la naturaleza en su mejor y bello estado, una lugar obligado para ir cuando estas en Bariloche.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to enjoy a break with family, friends or alone, nature in its best and beautiful state, a must-see place when you are in Bariloche.

review_text: Una subida de 1 km un poco exigida en subida pero vale la pena llegar a los dos miradores. Hermosa vista de las bahias.
review_translated_text: A 1 km climb that is a bit demanding on the way up but it is worth reaching the two viewpoints. Beautiful view of the bays.

review_text: Una maravilla, para descansar y relajar....
review_translated_text: A wonder, to rest and relax....

review_text: Vale la pena la subida. No representa gran desafio el camino, solo que por momento es bastante en subida. De igual forma, vale la pena la vista desde los miradores
review_translated_text: Its worth the climb. The path does not represent much of a challenge, it is just that at the moment it is quite uphill. Likewise, the view from the viewpoints is worth it.

review_text: Es un Lugar sonado para estar disfrutando del agua clara y el tiempo patagonico. Esta bien aprovechado su espacio para diversas actividades!
review_translated_text: It is a dream place to be enjoying the clear water and the Patagonian weather. Its space is well used for various activities!

review_text: Lugar encantador, no te lo pierdas
review_translated_text: Lovely place, dont miss it

review_text: En el puerto podes visitar tanto la bahia mansa como la brava. Ideal visitar ambas. El paisaje es excelente. Senti la naturaleza.
review_translated_text: In the port you can visit both the gentle and brave bays. Ideal to visit both. The landscape is excellent. I felt nature.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, una vista increible!!  vale la pena la caminata! Si estas en Villa lo tenes que hacer!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, an incredible view!! its worth the walk! If you are in Villa you have to do it!

review_text: Hermoso lugar .. donde podes disfrutar de la playa y tomarte unos buenos mates hay restoranes y varias empresas pera contratar paseos por el lago, tambien  hay un museo de canoas antiguas, excelente lugar para pasar la tarde y refrescarse un poco
review_translated_text: Beautiful place.. where you can enjoy the beach and have some good mates, there are restaurants and several companies to hire trips around the lake, there is also a museum of old canoes, an excellent place to spend the afternoon and cool off a little

review_text: Hermosa playa , hay estacionamiento , banos publicos muy limpios
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach, there is parking, very clean public bathrooms

review_text: Hermoso lugar,  playa tranquila con gente pero se puede estar bien. Tiene mucha sombra y tiene estacionamiento grande a unos mts de alli. Super recomendable para pasar una tarde
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, quiet beach with people but you can be fine. It has a lot of shade and has a large parking lot a few meters away. Super recommended to spend an afternoon

review_text: Hermoso paisaje, te dan ganas de quedarte hay
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape, makes you want to stay there

review_text: Excelente el recorrido, el lugar precioso, muy linda excursion
review_translated_text: Excellent tour, beautiful place, very nice excursion

review_text: Hermoso lugar, muy tranquilo. Si el clima esta lindo te podes meter al lago, y a su vez tenes varias opciones para andar en barcos, veleros, kayak o catamatan
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, very quiet. If the weather is nice you can go to the lake, and at the same time you have several options to ride in boats, sailboats, kayak or catamatan

review_text: Hermoso lugar,hay varias embarcaciones por lo que recomiendo si la idea es hacer playa ir a la Brava.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, there are several boats so I recommend if the idea is to go to the beach to go to La Brava.

review_text: Lugar maravilloso, ideal para tomar unos mates a la orilla del lago.
review_translated_text: Wonderful place, ideal for having some mates on the shore of the lake.

review_text: una playa hermosa, con fauna de patos , vista de fondo de pantallas y unos barquitos que terminan de adornar el paisaje
review_translated_text: a beautiful beach, with duck fauna, a view of the wallpaper and some little boats that finish adorning the landscape

review_text: Hermoso lugar!!! Para almorzar les recomiendo Viejos Tiempos, se come muy bien y los precios son accesibles!!!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!!! For lunch I recommend Viejos Tiempos, the food is very good and the prices are affordable!!!

review_text: Una playa muy amplia de arena de piedra y agua extremadamente fria. En temporada de verano suele llenarse bastante y es dificil estacionar. Tambien podes encontrar numerosas excursiones tanto desde alli como desde Bahia brava que esta aproximadamente a 200m en la direccion contraria, botes a pedal, kayak y alquiler de bicicletas, ademas de un pequeno museo regional. Hay variedad de restaurantes pequenos y una feria artesanal sobre la misma plazoleta.
review_translated_text: A very wide beach of stone sand and extremely cold water. In the summer season it tends to get quite crowded and parking is difficult. You can also find numerous excursions both from there and from Bahia Brava, which is approximately 200m in the opposite direction, pedal boats, kayaks and bicycle rentals, as well as a small regional museum. There are a variety of small restaurants and a craft fair on the same square.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, iria mil veces mas. Arena suabe, agua clara y lindo para pasar la tarde. Perfecto para dar un paseo tranqui en kayak.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, I would go a thousand times more. Soft sand, clear water and a nice place to spend the afternoon. Perfect for a quiet kayak ride.

review_text: Todo el camino hacia el mirador es muy bonito, con hermosas vistas al lago, frondosa vegetacion. El camino es de muy baja dificultad, por lo que se puede realizar sin problemas.
review_translated_text: The entire way to the viewpoint is very beautiful, with beautiful views of the lake, lush vegetation. The path is of very low difficulty, so it can be done without problems.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar para tomar unos mates y mirar el lago
review_translated_text: Very nice place to have some mates and look at the lake

review_text: Un lugar muy tranquilo, pacifico, y con unas vistas hermosas, de ahi se puede tomar el ferri hacia el bosque de arrayanes, el cual sale $800, estamos hablando de septiembre 2018,  lugar para almorzar con la paz de una lago totalmente calmo
review_translated_text: A very quiet, peaceful place, with beautiful views, from there you can take the ferry to the myrtle forest, which costs $800, we are talking about September 2018, a place to have lunch with the peace of a totally calm lake

review_text: Un lugar hermoso para disfrutar llenar los ojos y el alma de lugares hermosos de nuestro pais
review_translated_text: A beautiful place to enjoy filling your eyes and soul with beautiful places in our country.

review_text: Bellisimo lugar. Hay un puerto de donde salen las excursiones al bosque de arrayanes
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. There is a port where excursions to the myrtle forest leave

review_text: Muy lindo lugar para relajarse y banarse, tiene guardavidas y hay sobra.
review_translated_text: Very nice place to relax and bathe, it has lifeguards and there is plenty.

review_text: Hermoso lugar para pasar un rato y disfrutar la tranquilidad.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to spend some time and enjoy the tranquility.

review_text: Una bahia hermosa que puede contemplarse desde el mirador que se llega desde sendero del bosque de los arrayanes de facil acceso sobre el puerto de villa la angostura
review_translated_text: A beautiful bay that can be seen from the viewpoint that is reached from the Arrayanes forest path with easy access over the port of Villa La Angostura.

review_text: Maravilloso lugar. Para volver siempre!
review_translated_text: Wonderful place. To always return!

review_text: Hermosos paisajes, bello lugar
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscapes, beautiful place

review_text: Paraiso!
review_translated_text: Paradise!

review_text: Hermoso lugar, vale la pena llegar hasta alli. Pasamos a conocer VLA y estas a 10 min del  centro
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, worth getting there. We went to visit VLA and you are 10 minutes from the center

review_text: Es un paraiso. Muy lindo para nadar y tomar sol..super tranquila
review_translated_text: Its a paradise. Very nice for swimming and sunbathing...super quiet

review_text: Al lugar podes llegar muy facilmente caminando desde el centro de la ciudad, vistas indescriptibles.
review_translated_text: You can reach the place very easily by walking from the city center, indescribable views.

review_text: Sendero de unos 700 metros de muy facil acceso. Tiene unas lindas vistas del lago y nos permite conocer un poco mas sobre las especies de flora que hay en el parque.
review_translated_text: Path of about 700 meters with very easy access. It has beautiful views of the lake and allows us to learn a little more about the species of flora that are in the park.

review_text: Hermoso lugar pra ir a fotografiar los diferentes paisajes
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to go photograph the different landscapes

review_text: Hermoso, paisaje impresionante, agua cristalina. Cerca de la ciudad y tiene asfalto para llegar. Eso si, ir temprano para estacionar. Hay banos publicos cerca de la feria de artesanos.
review_translated_text: Beautiful, impressive landscape, crystal clear water. Close to the city and has asphalt to get there. Of course, go early to park. There are public toilets near the crafts fair.

review_text: La mansa y la Brava son UNA.. estan pegadas y ambas son tremendamente bellas. Las separa un estacionamiento muy bonito.
review_translated_text: The meek and the Brave are ONE... they are close and both are tremendously beautiful. A very nice parking lot separates them.

review_text: Una belleza indescriptible todos nuestros lagos del sur, verdaderamente es el paraiso en la tierra!!!!!
review_translated_text: All our southern lakes are indescribably beautiful, truly paradise on earth!!!!!

review_text: Esta vez fuimos de noche, lugar obligatorio para visitar en Villa por su belleza, su agua calma, transparente, su muelle amplio, casi siempre con algun turista sacando fotos. Vale la pena conocerlo!!
review_translated_text: This time we went at night, a mandatory place to visit in Villa for its beauty, its calm, transparent water, its wide pier, almost always with a tourist taking photos. Its worth knowing!!

review_text: Hermoso lugar , el color del agua es increible , hasta nos pudimos meter e hicimos el camino de los miradores. Muy bello !
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, the color of the water is incredible, we were even able to get in and take the path to the viewpoints. Very beautiful !

review_text: Uno de los lugares mas bonitos que tuve la suerte de conocer, un remanso de paz y vistas increibles.
review_translated_text: One of the most beautiful places I was lucky enough to know, a haven of peace and incredible views.

review_text: Es un lindo lugar para pasar el rato tomando mates cerca del centro de La Angostura.
review_translated_text: It is a nice place to spend time drinking mates near the center of La Angostura.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar. Relax.
review_translated_text: Very nice place. Relax.

review_text: Hermoso lugar se accede por aqui al Parque Nacional los Arrayanes donde si se paga entrada
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, you access the Arrayanes National Park through here, where you pay an entrance fee.

review_text: El nombre lo dice, es super tranquilo. Hermoso para pasar el dia, la playa es divina. El agua fria, obvio
review_translated_text: The name says it, it is super quiet. Beautiful to spend the day, the beach is divine. Cold water, obviously

review_text: Hermoso! No necesitas un pulmon extra para llegar al mirador, de agradece. Recomendacion: llevar zapatillas y bateria para las fotos. Es mejor hacerlo llegada la tarde xq la altura y el sol dificultan la subida. Y mucho off.
review_translated_text: Beautiful! You dont need an extra lung to get to the viewpoint, thank you. Recommendation: bring sneakers and drums for photos. It is better to do it in the afternoon because the altitude and the sun make the climb difficult. And a lot of off.

review_text: Lugar imperdible de villa la angostura, ambas bahias y el inicio del sendero del bosque de arrayanes...
review_translated_text: Unmissable place in Villa La Angostura, both bays and the beginning of the myrtle forest trail...

review_text: hermoso agua transparente hice excursion a Arrayanes
review_translated_text: beautiful transparent water I took an excursion to Arrayanes

review_text: Espectacular increible y tranquilo, un lugar ideal para disfrutar del senderismo, deportes acuaticos , y la naturaleza en su maxima expresion.
review_translated_text: Spectacular, incredible and quiet, an ideal place to enjoy hiking, water sports, and nature at its best.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, muy tranquilo. Optimo para unos matecitos
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, very quiet. Optimal for some mates

review_text: Excelente vista. No te cansas de mirar. La caminata empinada puede ser exigente pero lo vale totalmente
review_translated_text: Excellent view. You dont get tired of looking. The steep hike can be demanding but is totally worth it

review_text: Muy linda. Dentro de la ciudad quizas la segunda mejor playa
review_translated_text: Very cute. Within the city perhaps the second best beach

review_text: Fuimos para recorrer en catamaran, para reservar las entradas fuimos a Greenleaf turismo en villa la angostura, de ahi al puerto bahia mansa el precio del catamaran ida y vuelta sale 4k y la entrada al parque depende, con Carnet de discapacidad, jubilacion o de estudiante hay un gran descuento ya que la entrada al parque nacional sale (1800$) de ahi es hermoso el recorrido en el lago Nahuel Huapi, se visito la casita del te en total (1800$ en 2 te y un cafe con leche, 3 alfajores de chocolate) hay mas opciones para pedir (Rogel, lemon pie y creo un brownie) la casita del te se suele llenar demasiado, se puede ir directamente sin recorrer el parque arrayanes o hacer la caminata de 800m o para quienes no quieren o no pueden recorrer los 800m tienen otro camino mas corto, en total tres opciones para elegir, el tour es guiado y la guia los va a ir a buscar si es que es necesario para volver al catamaran, se puede comprar esta excursion desde puerto panuelo o directamente en Bariloche, se puede dejar el auto cerca el puerto hay como un mini estacionamiento sin cargo
review_translated_text: We went to tour by catamaran, to reserve tickets we went to Greenleaf tourism in Villa La Angostura, from there to the Bahia Mansa port the price of the catamaran round trip is 4k and the entrance to the park depends, with a disability card, retirement or As a student there is a great discount since the entrance to the national park costs ($1800) from there the tour to Lake Nahuel Huapi is beautiful, the tea house was visited in total ($1800 for 2 teas and a coffee with milk, 3 chocolate alfajores) there are more options to order (Rogel, lemon pie and I create a brownie) the tea house usually gets too crowded, you can go directly without visiting the arrayanes park or taking the 800m walk or for those who dont want to or They cannot travel the 800m, they have another shorter route, a total of three options to choose from, the tour is guided and the guide will pick them up if necessary to return to the catamaran, you can buy this excursion from Puerto Hanko or directly in Bariloche, you can leave your car near the port, there is like a mini parking lot free of charge

review_text: Descubrir esta maravilla natural me dejo enamorada de Villa La Angostura. Un paisaje de suenos, pensado solamente para peliculas o documentales.  Y lo asombroso de esto, es que lo tenemos en Argentina. La vista integrada de geografia y hombre, construccion y naturaleza, es algo que  no podemos dejar de ver. Seguro volveremos, un proyecto vacacional obligado!!!
review_translated_text: Discovering this natural wonder left me in love with Villa La Angostura. A landscape of dreams, designed only for films or documentaries. And the amazing thing about this is that we have it in Argentina. The integrated view of geography and man, construction and nature, is something we cannot help but see. We will surely return, a must-visit vacation project!

review_text: Linda playa de arena volcanica, se puede entrar sin problemas, casi no hay piedras. Hay guardavidas. Banos publicos en muy buen estado. Alquiler de Kayak pasando el muelle para el lado de la angostura (1000$/h por kayak de 1 persona, 1500/h para 2). Buceo con instructor y entrenamiento ($7500). Trekking a los miradores, dificultad media, abierto durante todo el dia (1km). El trekking al bosque de arrayanes (11km) cierra a las 14 hs. Son 3 hs caminando de ida y 3 de vuelta. En bici, cierra a las 15, dificultad alta. En ambos casos se puede regresar en ferry. El ultimo ferry sale de ida 15:45. Recomiendo ir temprano.
review_translated_text: Beautiful volcanic sand beach, you can enter without problems, there are almost no stones. There are lifeguards. Public bathrooms in very good condition. Kayak rental passing the dock to the narrow side ($1000/h for a kayak for 1 person, 1500/h for 2). Diving with instructor and training ($7500). Trekking to the viewpoints, medium difficulty, open all day (1km). The trek to the myrtle forest (11km) closes at 2 p.m. Its 3 hours walking there and 3 hours back. By bike, it closes at 3pm, high difficulty. In both cases you can return by ferry. The last ferry leaves at 15:45. I recommend going early.

review_text: Desde ahi podes contratar embarcaciones con capacidad para 10 personas que te llevan hasta Bosques de Arrayanes. Es genial

review_text: Bello lugar ! Para estar mirando un rato largo la bahia, sus pequenas playas y embarcaciones que por alli se desplazan. Aguas claras de distintas tonalidades, aire fresco y puro. El muelle es amplio desde donde se pueden tomar fotos estupendas
review_translated_text: Beautiful place ! To spend a long time looking at the bay, its small beaches and the boats that move there. Clear waters of different shades, fresh and pure air. The pier is wide from where you can take great photos

review_text: Una playa muy linda para visitar dentro del Parque Nacional

review_text: Es hermosa y tranquilo ... un lugar perfecto para relajarse

review_text: Tanto la Bahia Mansa como la Bahia Brava son hermosos lugares. Super tranquilo y familiares, un entorno natural increible. Son el punto de partido para el sendero que te lleva (12km) hasta el bosque de arrayanes. En ambas bahias hay puerto desde donde salen diferentes excursiones
review_translated_text: Both Mansa Bay and Brava Bay are beautiful places. Super quiet and family-friendly, an incredible natural environment. They are the starting point for the path that takes you (12km) to the myrtle forest. In both bays there is a port from where different excursions depart.

review_text: Lindo lugar, apacible tranquilo, natural, para respirar aire puro y fresco. Muy hermoso, el agua es cristalina. Cuenta con servicios de excursiones, banos y paseos en barcos... recomendado 100%. Pura naturaleza. Con contrastes y matices increibles.
review_translated_text: Nice place, peaceful, natural, to breathe pure and fresh air. Very beautiful, the water is crystal clear. It has excursion services, baths and boat rides... 100% recommended. Pure nature. With incredible contrasts and nuances.

review_text: El lugar cuenta con cabanas muy pintorescas y jardines cuidados. Es facil transitar por alli sin perderse y los caminos no son dificiles de recorrer con el auto. Se puede acceder a una playa publica de unos 200 o 300 metros muy bien mantenida.
review_translated_text: The place has very picturesque cabins and well-kept gardens. It is easy to get around without getting lost and the roads are not difficult to navigate by car. You can access a public beach of about 200 or 300 meters that is very well maintained.

review_text: Hermosos paisajes de montana.

review_text: La Bahia Mansa queda muy cerca del centro de Villa la Angostura. Fui caminando y me tomo 45 minutos, sin esfuerzo. Las vistas son de ensueno y, aunque el lugar es pequeno, hay espacio para apreciar la belleza de la naturaleza. Hay una pequena plaza, ademas, en donde sirven cafes, cervezas y comida ligera. 100% recomendado!
review_translated_text: Bahia Mansa is very close to the center of Villa la Angostura. I walked and it took me 45 minutes, without effort. The views are dreamlike and, although the place is small, there is space to appreciate the beauty of nature. There is also a small square where they serve coffee, beers and light food. 100% recommended!

review_text: El lugar cuenta con una playita increible para quienes disfrutan de tomar sol y meterse al lago. Detras un bosque nativo, donde podran hacer varios recorridos. Se recomienda el mirador Brazo Norte desde donde tendran una excelente vista a la Bahia y tambien a todos los cerros de la zona.

The Brazo Norte viewpoint is recommended from where you will have an excellent view of the Bay and also all the hills in the area.

review_text: Hermoso lugar!

review_text: Un hermoso sendero para disfrutar junto a la familia. Bien delimitado, muy cuidado. Las tortas y el chocolate caliente de la Casita de te impresionantes! Estuvimos a principio de ano que nos recibio con lluvia y frio(por eso chocolate caliente).
review_translated_text: A beautiful trail to enjoy with the family. Well defined, very careful. The cakes and hot chocolate at the Tea House are amazing! We were there at the beginning of the year when we were greeted with rain and cold (hence hot chocolate).

review_text: una playa de ensueno, con la mejor vista que el paisaje de los lagos neuquinos te puede dar

review_text: hermosa bahia, con playas calmas y reparo del viento hay muelle, catamaranes y restaurantes, alquiler de Kayak y paseos en velero. el agua es fria pero muy linda

review_text: El paseo por bahia Mansa y bahia Brava se puede hacer caminando, realmente estan muy cerca una de la otra. A cualquiera de las dos se llega por el Boulevard Nahuel Huapi al fondo y se puede estacionar en la zona de la oficina de turismo. Bahia San Patricio, es la conocida por todos como Bahia Mansa. Como se pueden imaginar por el nombre sus aguas son calmas y totalmente transparentes. En la playa se pueden alquilar kayaks, paseos de lancha e incluso alquilar un velero. La playa de Puerto Bahia Brava tiene un muelle desde el cual se pueden realizar las excursiones al Parque Nacional Los Arrayanes. Tambien podes embarcarte para recorrer el Nahuel Huapi y salir en botes que hacen recorridos, excursiones de pesca y paseos durante el dia. El viento provoca un oleaje un poco intenso. Lo lindo de este lugar es el entorno natural y sus atardeceres de verano, imperdibles.
review_translated_text: The walk through Mansa Bay and Brava Bay can be done on foot, they are really very close to each other. You can reach either of the two via Nahuel Huapi Boulevard at the end and you can park in the tourist office area. Bahia San Patricio is known to everyone as Bahia Mansa. As you can imagine from the name, its waters are calm and totally transparent. On the beach you can rent kayaks, boat rides and even rent a sailboat. The beach of Puerto Bahia Brava has a pier from which you can take excursions to the Los Arrayanes National Park. You can also embark to tour the Nahuel Huapi and go out on boats that take tours, fishing excursions and walks during the day. The wind causes a slightly intense wave. The beauty of this place is the natural environment and its summer sunsets, unmissable.

review_text: UN LUGAR LLENO DE PAZ. ES MAGICO
review_translated_text: A PLACE FULL OF PEACE. ITS MAGIC

review_text: Un lugar paradisiaco,  donde se pueden realizar actividades nauticas tales como alquiler de botes a pedal, kayak, paseos en veleros, paseos lacustres en muni cruceros. Hay un paseo gastronomico y mucha tranquilidad.  Desde la bahia se encuentra el acceso a la peninsula que tiene el sendero de 15km hasta el bosque de arrayanes. Sendero que tambien nos lleva en si inicio a los miradores, con un trekking de baja dificultad apto para ser visitado en familia.
review_translated_text: A paradisiacal place, where you can do nautical activities such as pedal boat rentals, kayaking, sailing trips, lake trips on muni cruises. There is a gastronomic walk and a lot of tranquility. From the bay there is access to the peninsula that has the 15km trail to the myrtle forest. Trail that also takes us at the beginning to the viewpoints, with a low difficulty trek suitable to be visited with the family.

review_text: Super lindo, habian unos patitos dando vueltas.

review_text: Hermoso lugar como todo el sur argentino. Simplemente hermoso

review_text: Hermoso paisaje. Un dia maravilloso lleno de paz
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape. A wonderful day full of peace

review_text: Quede cautivada con su belleza
review_translated_text: I was captivated by its beauty

review_text: No dudes, vale la pena ir.

review_text: Precioso lugar, mucha paz y serenidad. Ideal para quien disfruta y ama la naturaleza. IMPERDIBLE
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, a lot of peace and serenity. Ideal for those who enjoy and love nature. SAFETY PIN

review_text: Viajamos en el Catamaran Futaleufu. Una Embarcacion muy preparada y equipada con todo para conocer el Nahuel Huapi. Muy segura y con espacio para ver y sentir el viento. La guia,  ultra amable y bien formada. Conciencia ecologica y seriedad por el cuidado del lago y bosques. El precio, justo y la experiencia no tiene nada igual. El lago, conmovedor. El bosque de arrayanes,  precioso y unico. La guia nos hizo aprender muchas cosas. Una chica saca buenas fotos ( caras) para guardar el recuerdo. Lo unico que al volver suben otros pasajeros que no son los mismos de ida. Chicos de escuela menos interesados y descuidados. El viaje dura tres horas y hacen dos viajes al dia. Se puede comer alli mismo antes de salir: recomiendo PORTO SEGURO. Se almuerza de diez.
review_translated_text: We traveled on the Catamaran Futaleufu. A boat very prepared and equipped with everything to know the Nahuel Huapi. Very safe and with space to see and feel the wind. The guide, ultra friendly and well trained. Ecological awareness and seriousness in caring for the lake and forests. The price is fair and the experience has nothing like it. The lake, moving. The myrtle forest, beautiful and unique. The guide made us learn many things. A girl takes good photos (faces) to keep the memory. The only thing is that when they return, other passengers get on that are not the same ones on the way out. Less interested and careless school kids. The trip lasts three hours and they make two trips a day. You can eat right there before leaving: I recommend PORTO SEGURO. Lunch is served at ten.

review_text: Un lugar increible como todo el pasaje al rededor, con posibilidad de pagar un viaje en bote o kayak para ingresar al lago.. Entrada libre y gratuita, con varias opciones para comer cerca

Es preciosa. Se puede tomar mate ahi a la tardecita e incluso si se animan, meterse (esta fria como todos los lagos de la Patagonia pero en mi opinion vale la pena). El agua es mega limpia.

review_text: Bahia la mansa esta dentro del parque nacional. Yo hice el recorrido saliendo desde el kilometro 1 hasta el 12 caminando. El destino es bosque de arrayanes. A la vuelta tome un buque en el puerto de un particular vale mas barato que el. Monopolio de barcos que sale. De ahi.

review_text: Una vista excepcional del lago y sus alrededores, para llegar alli hay que recorrer un camino de montana corto (Se puede hacer en alrededor de 40 minutos caminando con ninos) pero bastante empinado. Muy recomendable

The upper apartments have views of the lake. recommendable

Recomiendo entrar al parque nacional arrayanes por el acceso peatonal y hacer ese sendero. El precio es elevado. $800 por persona ida y vuelta para residentes argentinos.

I recommend entering the Arrayanes National Park through the pedestrian access and taking that path. The price is high. $800 per person round trip for Argentine residents.

review_text: To get there you have to travel about 700 meters. uphill, once there you choose to continue straight to the myrtle forest (11 km. medium difficulty), to the left to the Bahia Mansa viewpoint (200 meters) or to the right to the North Arm viewpoint (200 meters). Worth the effort.
