review_text: Anduve caminando pir orilla del La. Nahuel Huapi, en Va. La angostura, Nquen, se llega a Bahia Mansa de un lado y solo unifo por un tiempo de tierra firme, separa a la Peninsula de Quetrihue de la zona terrestre donde esta asentada VLAngostura y se puede pasar a la otra Bahia. Desde ambas partes, parten Catamaranes hacia la punta Sur de la Peninsula Quetrihue.
review_translated_text: I was walking along the banks of the La. Nahuel Huapi, in Va. The narrowness, Nquen, you reach Bahia Mansa from one side and only for a while unified from the mainland, it separates the Quetrihue Peninsula from the land area where VLAngostura is located and you can go to the other Bay. From both sides, Catamarans depart towards the southern tip of the Quetrihue Peninsula.

review_text: Quisimos hacer la experiencia en bici a los Arrayanes y la verdad si no estan acostumbrados no es recomendable, tienen que ir levantando la bici , o sea cargarla porque hay escalones, raices, el sendero es muy chico y si no la tenes clara lo mas probable es que te caigas. Si, estan en forma pueden hacerlo caminando muy tranquilos descansando, pero tenes que estar en condiciones optimas. Con chicos no es recomendable ir. A no ser que se tomen el barquito a la vuelta, o vayan y regresen caminando. Pero son 130 cuadras aprox todas cuesta arriba.
review_translated_text: We wanted to do the experience by bike in Los Arrayanes and the truth is that if you are not used to it, it is not recommended, you have to lift the bike, that is, carry it because there are steps, roots, the path is very small and if you are not clear, most likely is that you fall. Yes, they are in shape, they can do it walking very calmly and resting, but you have to be in optimal condition. It is not recommended to go with children. Unless they take the boat on the way back, or walk back and forth. But it is approximately 130 blocks, all uphill.

review_text: Beautiful place! very quiet and with incredible views, steps from the myrtle forest and with several catamaran/boat excursions that you can take to navigate Lake Nahuel Huapi and to learn a little more about how beautiful it is! Very good service, very friendly people!
Un lugar magico, su lago y montanas   !!
review_translated_text: A magical place, its lake and mountains   !!

review_text: Bellisimo!! No dejen de visitarlo, sus aguas transparentes, el paisaje inmejorable, lugar para compartir unos buenas charlas y mates al aire libre y puro
review_translated_text: Beautiful!! Be sure to visit it, its transparent waters, the unbeatable landscape, a place to share good talks and mates in the open and pure air.

review_text: Hermoso. Un lugar repleto de naturaleza y tranquilidad para relajar, tomar mates, disfrutar de la calma y pasar una tarde super relajante

You dont have to pay to just do the trail to the Mirador. If you want to take a trail of around 7 hours through the park, you have to pay. In October 2019 the cost for foreigners is 400 Argentine pesos. Its very worth it. The view is surreally beautiful!

review_text: Bellisimoo

Muy linda vista! Vale la pena aun estando nublado. Son 20 minutos de subida algo empinado. Unico inconveniente es que el mismo camino el cual era angosto tambien se usa como sendero para bicicletas y se complica tanto para quien va caminando como para el ciclista.
review_translated_text: Very nice view! Its worth it even if its cloudy. It is a 20 minute somewhat steep climb. The only drawback is that the same path, which was narrow, is also used as a bicycle path and becomes complicated for both the walker and the cyclist.

review_text: Hermoso para apreciar los paisajes, y el lugar. Mi hijo se metio al agua y le encanto.
review_translated_text: Beautiful to appreciate the landscapes, and the place. My son got into the water and loved it.

review_text: Beautiful place What I liked most was the Isthmus of Quetrihue and the viewpoint
Hermoso lugar para pasar el dia..la vista inigualable!! Podes tomar sol o hacer kayak . Es una playa sin viento ideal!! Lo unico que es poco extensa asi que se llena de gente.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to spend the day...the unmatched view!! You can sunbathe or kayak. It is an ideal windless beach!! The only thing is that it is not very extensive so it gets crowded.

review_text: Hermoso lugar para disfrutar del silencio y la calma del lugar.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to enjoy the silence and calm of the place.

review_text: Precioso el lugar!!! Rodeado de tanta naturaleza.... lago con aguas turquesas, transparentes, las montanas con esos distintos tonos de verde y el inmenso cielo azul celeste con el calido brillo del sol ... es una gran belleza para disfrutar a pleno en familia o con amigos !! Nos encanto Bahia Mansa!!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!!! Surrounded by so much nature.... lake with turquoise, transparent waters, mountains with those different shades of green and the immense azure blue sky with the warm glow of the sun... it is a great beauty to fully enjoy with family or with friends !! We loved Bahia Mansa!!

review_text: Hermoso lugar! En Bahia mansa se pueden alquilar Kayaks y esta a pocos metros de la zona gastronomica y tambien de Bahia Brava. No pongo 5 estrellas porque es terrible la invasion de chaquetas amarillas que hay y su picadura es muy dolorosa
review_translated_text: Beautiful place! In Bahia Mansa you can rent Kayaks and it is a few meters from the gastronomic area and also from Bahia Brava. I dont give 5 stars because the invasion of yellow jackets is terrible and their bite is very painful.

review_text: Es una playita chica pero bastante bonita, cerca de la entrada del Parque Nacional los Arrayanes, en Villa la Angostura. Cuando fuimos el agua estaba muy helada, no se si siempre es tan asi. Muy cerca esta Bahia Brava, que de brava tiene solo el nombre, y me gusto un poco mas. Incluso el agua alli estaba menos fria. Te recomiendo visitar ambas, pero quedarte mas tiempo en la Brava.
review_translated_text: It is a small but quite pretty beach, near the entrance to the Arrayanes National Park, in Villa la Angostura. When we went the water was very cold, I dont know if its always like that. Very close is Bahia Brava, which only has its name as brava, and I liked it a little more. Even the water there was less cold. I recommend you visit both, but stay longer in Brava.

review_text: Muy lindo!! Estuvimos ahi toda la tarde. La playa de estacionamiento estaba llena pero para nuestra sorpresa la bahia no tan colapsada. Esta pegada al muelle que conduce al bosque de los Arrayanes y probablemente por eso tantos autos en la zona!! Recomiendo este lugar!
review_translated_text: Very pretty!! We were there all afternoon. The parking lot was full but to our surprise the bay was not so crowded. It is attached to the pier that leads to the Arrayanes forest and that is probably why so many cars in the area!! I recommend this place!

review_text: The beach is really calm, there are public services, kayak rental, the view has nothing to envy a National Geographic photo shot. Its really near other spots to enjoy so come planning to keep moving and get to know different places
Belleza natural espectacular. Desde la navegacion que contratamos se ve un paisaje maravilloso. Los guias muy atentos y amables. Hay catamaranes y embarcaciones privadas para contratar.
review_translated_text: Spectacular natural beauty. From the navigation we hired you can see a wonderful landscape. The guides are very attentive and friendly. There are catamarans and private boats to hire.

review_text: Precioso. Excelentes vistas. Incluso pudimos ver el arcoiris desde ahi. Muy limpio excepto por los cigarrillos que tira la gente irresponsable.
review_translated_text: Precious. Excellent views. We could even see the rainbow from there. Very clean except for the cigarettes that irresponsible people throw away.

review_text: Gran lugar para pasar el dia, tenes la playita y diferentes actividades para hacer. Tambien hay un parador de artesanos y al lado restos para comer.
review_translated_text: Great place to spend the day, you have the beach and different activities to do. There is also a craftsmens hostel and nearby restaurants.

review_text: Bueno si te pongo otro paisaje despues de una hora no sabrias de donde procede.. sitio como otros tantos, nada que resaltar. bonito, si. servicios adecuados, si. pero no emociona ni te cambia el espiritu.
review_translated_text: Well, if I give you another landscape, after an hour you wouldnt know where it came from... a place like many others, nothing to highlight. nice, yes. adequate services, yes. but it does not excite or change your spirit.

review_text: No es la mejor playa de Villa La Angostura, pero es bonita. Es pequena y suele estar llena de barcos. Desde alli sale uno de los barcos en excursion al Parque Nacional Arrayanes. En sus muelles pueden apreciarse los colores del lago de una manera magnifica. Ir al menos un rato.
review_translated_text: It is not the best beach in Villa La Angostura, but it is beautiful. It is small and usually full of boats. From there one of the boats leaves on an excursion to the Arrayanes National Park. On its docks you can see the colors of the lake in a magnificent way. Go at least for a while.

review_text: Linda vista, lugar tranquilo para ir a tomar mates. Se puede acceder facilmente. Pasamos dia domingo y habia algun evento en el pueblo por lo que se nos hizo dificil encontrar lugar para estacionar. Hay chicos que cuidan los autos.
review_translated_text: Nice view, quiet place to go have mates. It can be easily accessed. We spent Sunday and there was some event in town so it was difficult for us to find a parking space. There are guys who take care of the cars.

review_text: Lindo lugar para tomar unos mates, asi como para apreciar en paisaje. Desde ahi, estas a un paso para entrar al parque nacional arrayanes, y hacer un sendero muy lindo de 12 kms hasta el bosque de arrayanes
review_translated_text: Nice place to have some mates, as well as to appreciate the landscape. From there, you are just a step away from entering the Arrayanes National Park, and taking a very nice 12 km trail to the Arrayanes forest.

review_text: Desde ese lugar , partimos hacia el Bosque de Arrayanes . Se consigue los mejores precios .....lo recomiendo , si quieren visitar el bosque .  Un paisaje increible!
review_translated_text: From that place, we leave for the Arrayanes Forest. You get the best prices...I recommend it, if you want to visit the forest. An incredible landscape!

review_text: El agua es increible. Pocas veces vi algo parecido a esto. Lastima la playa tan chiquita y llena de barcos, lo que dificulta meterse al agua. Tiene un muelle al cual podes ir y disfrutar de la vista. Recomiendo caminar hasta bahia brava y quedarse ahi.
review_translated_text: The water is incredible. I have rarely seen anything like this. It hurts that the beach is so small and full of boats, which makes it difficult to get into the water. It has a dock where you can go and enjoy the view. I recommend walking to Bahia Brava and staying there.

review_text: Beautiful views of the lake from the dock. The visit to the Arrayanes park with the catamaran is recommended, if the sun is good it is ideal.

El camino del sendero de bosque de arrayanes arranca en el muelle de bahia brava. Si se quiere hacer todo el camino a pie son tres horas de ida y tres de vuelta, o se debe volver en barco. Para hacer el camino a pie el horario maximo de entrada es las 14 hs. En bici se puede entrar mas tarde. Otra opcion que es la RECOMENDABLE  para hacer con ninos o personas sin mucha preparacion para caminar tanto, es hacer solo el primer kilometro (en subida y con pendientes , pero se puede) el cual es sin costo y se puede entrar tambien pasadas las 14.00 hs. La.entrada del recorrido completo se paga , pero para residentes argentinos es menos de $300. Extranjeros 1800 Una vez subido ese primer kilometro se llega a dos miradores muy lindos. Desde uno de ellos se ve el istmo de quetrihue y la vista es bellisima !! Vale la pena! PD: los banos antes de comenzar el camino donde se paga la entrada estan bastante bien
review_translated_text: The myrtle forest trail starts at the Bahia Brava pier. If you want to do the entire way on foot, it is three hours there and three hours back, or you must return by boat. To do the route on foot, the maximum entry time is 2:00 p.m. By bike you can enter later. Another option that is RECOMMENDED to do with children or people without much preparation to walk so much, is to do only the first kilometer (uphill and with slopes, but it is possible) which is free of charge and you can also enter after 2:00 p.m. . The entrance fee for the entire tour is paid, but for Argentine residents it is less than $300. Foreigners 1800 Once you have climbed that first kilometer you reach two very beautiful viewpoints. From one of them you can see the isthmus of Quetrihue and the view is beautiful!! Its worth it! PS: the bathrooms before starting the path where you pay the entrance are quite good

review_text: Muy lindo lugar para pasar el dia, tiene unas vistas increibles
review_translated_text: Very nice place to spend the day, it has incredible views

review_text: Hermoso lugar!! Pero seria buenisimo que la gente respete la zona y vuelva con sus residuos
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!! But it would be great if people respected the area and returned with their waste.

review_text: Beautiful place! (2019) I returned this year, ideal to go with the family.
Lugar super tranquilo. Con variedad de atracciones y actividades acuaticas. El agua es muy fria pero aun asi hay quienes disfrutan de ella. Es apto para el ingreso al lago.
review_translated_text: Super quiet place. With a variety of attractions and water activities. The water is very cold but there are still those who enjoy it. It is suitable for entering the lake.

review_text: Bello y relajante lugar..para pasar un tremendo Dia de playa..
review_translated_text: Beautiful and relaxing place... to spend a tremendous day at the beach...

review_text: Hermoso lugar! Lago calmo, playa bastante amplia y una vista espectacular. A metros de la Bahia Brava.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place! Calm lake, fairly wide beach and a spectacular view. A few meters from Bahia Brava.

review_text: Hermosa vista desde cualquier angulo que se lo vea. Hay banos publicos, estacionamiento gratis, locales para sentarse a comer, tambien hay opcion de contratar servicio de traslado en barco hasta bosque de arrayanes, hay alquiler de bicicletas para recorrer todo el sendero por tierra que son 12 km solo la ida. Se puede adquirir la entrada al parque nacional via on line en la pagina oficial de parques nacionales. Tambien esta la opcion gratis del sendero de los miradores que son entre 2 y 3 km. Hay para todos los gustos. Los botecitos con pedales estaban pero el muchacho que alquilaba no estaba todavia. Me dijeron que no tiene horario fijo.
review_translated_text: Beautiful view from any angle you see it. There are public bathrooms, free parking, places to sit down to eat, there is also the option of hiring a boat transfer service to the myrtle forest, there is bicycle rental to travel the entire path by land, which is 12 km one way. You can purchase entry to the national park online on the official national parks website. There is also the free option of the viewpoint trail, which is between 2 and 3 km. There is something for everyone. The little pedal boats were there but the boy who rented them was not there yet. They told me they dont have fixed hours.

review_text: Un muy bonito lugar para visitar y pasar un rato contemplando el paisaje
review_translated_text: A very nice place to visit and spend some time contemplating the landscape

review_text: Es un lindo sendero sin tener que llegar a hacer todo el sendero, es gratuito. Es dificultoso para gente no entrenada, llevar agua y buen calzado, la vista de este mirador no es tan limpia como la del mirador brazo Norte.
review_translated_text: It is a nice trail without having to do the entire trail, it is free. It is difficult for untrained people to bring water and good footwear, the view from this viewpoint is not as clean as that of the North Arm viewpoint.

review_text: Linda playa para ir a pasar un dia tranquilo.  Lo bueno es que hay poco viento, lo malo es que tiene muchas embarcaciones sobre la costa que hacen que el paisaje no se pueda apreciar
review_translated_text: Nice beach to go to spend a quiet day. The good thing is that there is little wind, the bad thing is that there are many boats on the coast that make the landscape impossible to appreciate.

review_text: Hermosa playa de arena y deshielo, buena vista y tranquila! Se puede alquilar kayak, bucear, etc
review_translated_text: Beautiful sandy and melting beach, good view and quiet! You can rent kayak, dive, etc.

review_text: Muy linda vista. La playa esta limpia. Poco espacio para estacionar. Hay paradas de taxi. Se puede hacer paseos en catamaran que salen desde ahi. Se puede amarrar. Cercano a restorantes y confiterias (carisimo), bosque de Arrayanes y Bahia Brava. Los banos publicos cercanos son un asco.
review_translated_text: Very nice view. The beach is clean. Little space to park. There are taxi ranks. You can take catamaran rides that leave from there. It can be tied. Close to restaurants and sweet shops (very expensive), Myrtles forest and Bahia Brava. The nearby public bathrooms suck.

review_text: Beautiful place, super crystal clear water... Many nautical activities to implement... The only bad thing is the part of the beach you go to, there are a lot of stones, it is recommended to wear shoes... Then you are off.
Excelente playa para pasar el dia en villa langostura. Se permiten mascotas (Pets friendly)
review_translated_text: Excellent beach to spend the day in Villa Langostura. Pets allowed (Pets friendly)

review_text: Hermoso lugar, el muelle mantiene todavia sus anos de antiguedad y eso lo hace mas atractivo. Ofrecen excursiones y hay una agencia de informacion turistica a pocos metros. A 200 m en direccion contraria se encuentra el otro muelle tan hermoso como este. Eh ido infinidad de veces y no me canso de la hermosa vista y atracciones de Villa la Angostura. Super recomendable para ir en familia (en auto, en bici, o en bus)
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, the pier still maintains its years of age and that makes it more attractive. They offer excursions and there is a tourist information agency a few meters away. 200 m in the opposite direction is the other pier as beautiful as this one. Ive been countless times and I cant get enough of the beautiful views and attractions of Villa la Angostura. Super recommended to go as a family (by car, by bike, or by bus)

review_text: Hermoso. Lugar agradable y tranquilo. De alli salen excursiones
review_translated_text: Beautiful. Nice and quiet place. Excursions leave from there

review_text: Hermoso lugar , lo unico q no me gusto es q mucha gente no tiene la costumbre de llevarse la basura para tirarla donde corresponde. Sacando eso un Hermoso lugar para tomar unos mates
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, the only thing I didnt like is that many people are not in the habit of taking their garbage to throw it where it belongs. Taking that out, a beautiful place to have some mates

review_text: Hermoso lugar donde se puede navegar con kayak o bote a pedal. Se puede acceder a un recorrido a pie por el istmo que separa esta bahia de la Brava.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place where you can navigate with a kayak or pedal boat. You can access a walking tour of the isthmus that separates this bay from La Brava.

review_text: La primera parte del trayecto cuesta un poco, pero es lindo recorrido. La cantidad de arboles complica un poco la vision pero es parte del paisaje
review_translated_text: The first part of the journey costs a little, but it is a nice journey. The number of trees complicates the vision a little but it is part of the landscape

review_text: Hermoso paisaje de la bahia y una playa para pasar una linda tarde. Algunas personas no cuidan el lugar y se ven varios residuos en el suelo. Pero dentro de todo, un muy lindo lugar.
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape of the bay and a beach to spend a nice afternoon. Some people do not take care of the place and various waste is seen on the ground. But all in all, a very nice place.

review_text: Hermosa playa a metros del centro de la Villa. De aguas muy tranquilas. De ahi salen y llegan las excursiones nauticas a la Isla Victoria y al Bosque de Arrayanes.
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach meters from the center of the Villa. Very calm waters. From there the nautical excursions to Victoria Island and the Arrayanes Forest depart and arrive.

review_text: Hermoso lugar para nadar y tomar mates. Lo negativo muchos chicos gritando.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to swim and drink mates. The negative: many kids shouting.

review_text: Bahia donde se agarra el Catamaran para salir a Bosque de los Arrayanes. Linda tambien para pasear.
review_translated_text: Bay where you take the Catamaran to go out to Bosque de los Arrayanes. Also nice to walk.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar, nos toco llegar y que haya gente tomando mates en el lugar por lo que no habia mucho lugar. La vista esta un poco tapada por los arboles pero aun asi se puede ver bien.
review_translated_text: Very nice place, we had to arrive and there were people drinking mates in the place so there wasnt much space. The view is a little obscured by the trees but you can still see it well.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar, aguas claras
review_translated_text: Very nice place, clear waters

review_text: Es un lugar para disfrutar, no me gusto la ultima vez que habia mucha gente
review_translated_text: It is a place to enjoy, I did not like it the last time there were many people

review_text: Muy lindo lugar para ir a disfrutar del lago, poca gente. Lo unico que no es muy lindo es la arena volcanica que parece tierra.
review_translated_text: Very nice place to go to enjoy the lake, few people. The only thing that is not very pretty is the volcanic sand that looks like dirt.

review_text: Me gusto claramente y si venis a.la Villa, debes visitarlas a todas.
review_translated_text: I clearly liked it and if you come to the Villa, you must visit them all.

review_text: Lugar acogedor y bien atendido, para pasar lindos momentos con cosas ricas
review_translated_text: Cozy and well attended place, to spend beautiful moments with delicious things

review_text: Linda playa. Calma. De ahi parten las excursiones a bosque de arrayanes
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach. Calm. From there the excursions to the myrtle forest depart.

review_text: Es mucho mas entranable que el otro mirador. Vale la pena desviarse un poquito para verlo
review_translated_text: It is much more endearing than the other viewpoint. Its worth taking a little detour to see it.

review_text: Se puede llegar caminando o en bici desde el centro de VLA, acceso gratuito.
review_translated_text: It can be reached on foot or by bike from the center of VLA, free access.

review_text: Hermosa bahia con vista al lago. Parada obligada si visitas Villa La Angostura.
review_translated_text: Beautiful bay with lake view. A must stop if you visit Villa La Angostura.

review_text: Llegamos en excursion fue una parada rapida para sacar fotos. Hermoso y tranquilo lugar.
review_translated_text: We arrived on an excursion, it was a quick stop to take photos. Beautiful and quiet place.

review_text: Lindo lugar para pasar el dia  deberian  recomendar llevar agua  para hacer el circuito
review_translated_text: Nice place to spend the day, they should recommend bringing water to do the circuit

review_text: Bellisimo lugar para descansar y tener contacto con la naturaleza
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to rest and have contact with nature

review_text: El lugar es una maravilla natural. Los dias de semana es mas tranquilo que los fines que esta bastante lleno. Hay restaurantes y alguna que otra cafeteria para comer y tomar algo. Esta bien senalizado y hay banos publicos. Es un lindo circuito para ir con ninos pequenos. Lo unico criticable es que la zona del estacionamiento era un caos. Al no haber parcelas delimitadas muchos autos quedaron atrapados por otros que estacionaron mal, el estacionamiento es gratuito pero nadie controla.
review_translated_text: The place is a natural wonder. On weekdays it is quieter than on weekends when it is quite crowded. There are restaurants and the occasional cafeteria to eat and have a drink. It is well signposted and there are public bathrooms. It is a nice circuit to go with small children. The only thing to criticize is that the parking area was chaos. Since there were no delimited plots, many cars were trapped by others who parked incorrectly. Parking is free but no one controls it.

review_text: Bellisimo lugar como muchos lugares en patagonia pero destaca villa la angostura con sus posibilidades de estas doa bahias combinadas a la perfeccion
review_translated_text: Beautiful place like many places in Patagonia but Villa La Angostura stands out with its possibilities of these two bays combined to perfection

review_text: Buen lugar para hacer kayack y excursiones
review_translated_text: Good place for kayaking and excursions

review_text: Muy lindo lugar para hacer playa con unas vistas tremendas.  Ademas hay bares y artesanias muy bonito. No dejen de probar algo en A Rajatabla que vale la pena
review_translated_text: Very nice place to beach with tremendous views. There are also very nice bars and crafts. Dont forget to try something in A Rajatabla that is worth it

review_text: Hermoso lugar, tranquilo
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, quiet

review_text: Punto obligado para llevarse un recuerdo del hermoso paisaje.
review_translated_text: A must-see to take home a souvenir of the beautiful landscape.

review_text: Hermoso lugar bastante concurrido ...trato de ir siempre q voy en verano a Bariloche...
review_translated_text: Beautiful, quite busy place...I try to go every time I go to Bariloche in the summer...

review_text: Muy tranquilo ideal para stand up padel
review_translated_text: Very quiet ideal for stand up padel

review_text: Muy linda vista desde el muelle
review_translated_text: Very nice view from the pier

review_text: Muy lindo lugar
review_translated_text: Very nice place

review_text: A veces,no se puede trasmitir lo que se siente ante un lugar tan hermoso.
review_translated_text: Sometimes you cant convey what you feel in such a beautiful place.

review_text: Excellent views, great little walk. We enjoyed a boat ride to the end of the peninsula, then hiked back. I would do that again if I had the choice.
Bahia con veleros cayak botes catamaranes playa. Excelente par el descanso y el placer
review_translated_text: Bay with sailboats cayak boats catamarans beach. Excellent for rest and pleasure

review_text: Una playa excelente, muy linda
review_translated_text: An excellent beach, very beautiful

review_text: Hermoso lugar, muy tranquilo
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, very quiet

review_text: El lago era un espejo, agua fria para enero, poca gente, muy tranquilo, y quienes visitan el lugar tienen esa filosofia de tranquilidad y disfrutar, hay que ir temprano para no volverse loc@ con el estacionamiento, los tours de navegacion son caros, esta a 2 pasos de la entrada al bosque de arrayanes. Recomiendo mucho este lugar
review_translated_text: The lake was a mirror, cold water for January, few people, very quiet, and those who visit the place have that philosophy of tranquility and enjoyment, you have to go early to avoid going crazy with parking, the boating tours are expensive, It is 2 steps from the entrance to the myrtle forest. I highly recommend this place

review_text: Para descansar y disfrutar bellezas de nuestro pais
review_translated_text: To rest and enjoy the beauties of our country

review_text: Hermoso Lugar!!! Increible La Paz que hay ahi
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!!! Incredible peace there

review_text: Un lugar muy hermoso y tranquilo, al igual que la bahia brava. Imperdible en villa la angostura. El unico problema fue que no encontramos bano publico. Se encuentra a 4 km de villa la angostura.
review_translated_text: A very beautiful and quiet place, just like Brava Bay. Not to be missed in Villa La Angostura. The only problem was that we didnt find a public bathroom. It is located 4 km from Villa La Angostura.

review_text: Hermosa playa para remar y tomarte unos mates tranquis
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach to paddle and have some quiet mates

review_text: Un lindo lugar para disfrutar el entorno natural o subirse al catamaran hacia el bosque de arrayanes (servicio muy caro para mi gusto: 9000 argentinos ida y vuelta u 8000 argentinos un solo tramo).
review_translated_text: A nice place to enjoy the natural environment or get on the catamaran to the myrtle forest (very expensive service for my taste: 9,000 Argentines round trip or 8,000 Argentines for a single leg).

review_text: Increible paisaje... Quiza falta un poco de cuidado hacia los visitantes, explicandoles detalles de la travesia y que haya manera de solicitar ayuda si llegara a suceder algun imprevisto.
review_translated_text: Incredible landscape... Perhaps there is a lack of care towards visitors, explaining details of the journey and having a way to request help if something unforeseen were to happen.

review_text: Hermoso, exuberante, maravilla de la naturaleza. La Patagonia es de lo mejor que tiene Argentina.
review_translated_text: Beautiful, lush, wonder of nature. Patagonia is one of the best that Argentina has.

review_text: Muy linda y confortable para meterse
review_translated_text: Very nice and comfortable to get into

review_text: Lindo lugar para pasear en familia, existes bites que te pueden llevar al bosque de arrayanes que esta al lado, se puede hacer circuito de bicicleta moderado alto, no para ninos.
review_translated_text: Nice place to walk with the family, there are bites that can take you to the myrtle forest that is next door, you can do a moderately high bicycle circuit, not for children.

review_text: Espectacular lugar. Precioso
review_translated_text: Spectacular place. Precious

review_text: Lindo lugar para pasar el dia tomando unos mates y mirar el lago de paso y tirarse un chapuzon porque no? Lo unico dificil es encontrar estacionamiento despues, todo impecable.
review_translated_text: Nice place to spend the day having some mates and looking at the lake as you pass and taking a dip, why not? The only difficult thing is finding parking afterwards, everything is impeccable.

review_text: Parada obligada, Lucar hermosa.
review_translated_text: A must stop, beautiful Lucar.

review_text: Hermoso lugar, hermosa vista y el agua es totalmente transparente. Hay muchas abejas que hacen que la estadia en el lugar sea algo molesta. Le pongo solo 4 estrellas porque la parte mas linda de la bahia esta ocupada por barcos que se llevan lo mas lindo de la playa cuando quizas podrian estar tranquilamente en el puerto
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, beautiful view and the water is totally transparent. There are many bees that make the stay in the place somewhat annoying. I only give it 4 stars because the most beautiful part of the bay is occupied by boats that take away the most beautiful part of the beach when perhaps they could be calmly in the port

review_text: Hermoso lugar
review_translated_text: Beautiful place

review_text: Hermoso lugar para.descansar. muy lindas vistas y muy tranquilo
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to rest. very nice views and very quiet

review_text: El domingo pasado (27/11/2022) en Bahia Mansa embarcamos hacia el Bosque de Arrayanes en la peninsula de Quetrihue, el viaje en el Catamaran Futaleufu impecable y me saco el sombrero con la guia turistica por sus ricos conocimientos de historia y ecologia!! Muy buena experiencia por solo $5500 por persona + $800 para acceder al Parque Nacional. La excursion dura 3hs
review_translated_text: Last Sunday (11/27/2022) in Bahia Mansa we embarked towards the Arrayanes Forest on the Quetrihue peninsula, the trip on the Futaleufu Catamaran was impeccable and I take my hat off to the tourist guide for her rich knowledge of history and ecology! ! Very good experience for only $5500 per person + $800 to access the National Park. The excursion lasts 3 hours

review_text: Hermoso lugar.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place.

review_text: Muy linda vista, habria que hacerle mantenimiento a las maderas del puente, porque algunas estan un poco rotas...pero eso no impide de disfrutar de la vista. Desde alli sale la excursion a bosque de Arrayanes. Tambien se puede hacer a pie, con una duracion de 2hs aprox
review_translated_text: Very nice view, maintenance should be done on the wood of the bridge, because some are a little broken...but that doesnt stop you from enjoying the view. From there the excursion to the Arrayanes forest departs. It can also be done on foot, lasting approximately 2 hours.

review_text: Lugar sonado ideal para la familia!!
review_translated_text: Ideal dream place for the family!!

review_text: Hermosa la excursion a Bosque de Arrayanes pero el precio para ser temporada BAJA sumado a la entrada al parque me parece un poco excesivo... si elijes hacer un solo tramo e ir o volver a pie te cobran 2/3 del valor... me parece bastante injusto, pero no te la podes perder!
review_translated_text: The excursion to Bosque de Arrayanes is beautiful but the price for being LOW season added to the entrance to the park seems a little excessive to me... if you choose to do a single section and go or return on foot they charge you 2/3 of the value... It seems quite unfair to me, but you cant miss it!

review_text: bonito lugar para conocer, se puede ir caminando, tardas alrededor de unos 40 minutos desde el centro o puedes tomar la micro. Hay artesanias y lugares para comer.
review_translated_text: nice place to visit, you can walk, it takes around 40 minutes from the center or you can take the bus. There are crafts and places to eat.

review_text: Hermoso sitio, muy bien cuidado, limpio, ordenado. Realizamos una excursion en un ferry hasta Bosque de arrayanes, realmente hermoso, solo me parecio escaso el tiempo para estar en el bosque pero una hermosa experiencia. Recomendable para ir en familia.
review_translated_text: Beautiful site, very well maintained, clean, tidy. We took an excursion on a ferry to Arrayanes Forest, really beautiful, I just thought there was little time to be in the forest but it was a beautiful experience. Recommended to go with family.

review_text: Hermoso lugar! Con vistas espectaculares.  El sendero algo complicado, en especial en temporada alta, cdo hay muchos caminantes!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place! With spectacular views. The path is somewhat complicated, especially in high season, when there are many walkers!

review_text: El lugar es bellisimo. Playa amplia de piedra. El agua es un azul turquesa imponente. No mas fria que otros lagos como el Lacar. El ambiente es familiar. A 100 mt hay locales de comida donde se puede estacionar.Cerca de alli se encuentra el muelle para realizar activ de canotaje o excursiones Bosques los Arrayanes y paso por la Isla Victoria.(1hra de navegacion, 30/40 min en el lugar y regreso)
review_translated_text: The place is beautiful. Wide stone beach. The water is a stunning turquoise blue. No colder than other lakes like Lacar. The atmosphere is familiar. At 100 meters there are food places where you can park. Nearby is the dock for canoeing activities or excursions to Bosques los Arrayanes and passage through Isla Victoria. (1 hour of navigation, 30/40 minutes in the place and return )

review_text: Tal cual lo indica su nombre este es un lugar de sosiego. Posee una playa con arena, una extraordinaria vista del lago, su muelle, embarcaciones y el inefable bosque de arrayanes. Es imperdible el Museo Regional, donde se pueden ver dos canoas monoxilas de los pueblos que habitaban estos lugares. Lugar extraordinario de Argentina.
review_translated_text: As its name indicates, this is a place of peace. It has a sandy beach, an extraordinary view of the lake, its dock, boats and the ineffable myrtle forest. The Regional Museum is not to be missed, where you can see two monoxila canoes from the people who inhabited these places. Extraordinary place in Argentina.

review_text: Hermoso, pero ojo que cuesta la subida de 1km caminando si no estas en buen estado fisico, o si no llevas buen calzado para hacer trekking por que es muy resbaladizo. Faltaria senalizacion de la distancia que falta para llegar a los miradores y mejorar los parantes. Pero al final la vista es espectacular. Para ver los miradores no hay que pagar entrada al parque, pero...si van a rrecorrer el resto de los 11km hasta el bosque de arrayanes ahi si deberan pagarlo. Ojo si decides hacerlo en bicicleta tendras que cargarla bastante antes de poder hacer tramos andando
review_translated_text: Beautiful, but be careful that it is difficult to climb the 1km walk if you are not in good physical condition, or if you are not wearing good trekking shoes because it is very slippery. There would be a lack of signage of the distance left to reach the viewpoints and to improve the stops. But in the end the view is spectacular. To see the viewpoints you do not have to pay an entrance fee to the park, but...if you are going to travel the rest of the 11km to the myrtle forest, you will have to pay there. Be careful, if you decide to do it by bicycle, you will have to carry it a lot before you can walk sections.

review_text: Muy lindo y tranquilo
review_translated_text: Very nice and quiet

review_text: Muy agradable para pasar un buen rato,con vista hermosa
review_translated_text: Very nice to have a good time, with a beautiful view

review_text: Playa muy bonita. Podes hacer Kayak, los alquileres estar al rededor de $500 la media hora mas o menos. A la tarde empieza a dar mas la sombra del bosque y se pone fresco, es ideal para ir en la manana que esta el solcito, pero si el frio no es problema es ideal, hermosa y muy tranquila.
review_translated_text: Very nice beach. You can kayak, the rentals are around $500 per half hour or so. In the afternoon the shade of the forest begins to give more shade and it gets cool, it is ideal to go in the morning when the sun is shining, but if the cold is not a problem it is ideal, beautiful and very quiet.

review_text: Tiene una hermosa vista al muelle. Les recomiendo ir a este mirador al comienzo de la caminata, antes de encarar el camino a los bosques de arallanes, porque es muy empinada la subida. Y si lo hacen a la vuelta van a estar muertos y no lo van a disfrutar.
review_translated_text: It has a beautiful view of the pier. I recommend going to this viewpoint at the beginning of the walk, before facing the path to the arallanes forests, because the climb is very steep. And if they do it on the way back they will be dead and they will not enjoy it.

review_text: Hermoso! Muy tranquilo! No habia casi nadie cuando visitamos, se pueden hacer actividades en el agua como kayac. Aunque, el agua, nos parecio mas fria que en bahia brava. En los alrededores hay lugares para comer y es muy pintoresco para pasear. Hay una mini feria de artesanos, pero son muy poquitos puestos. Si alquilas una bici! Es genial para recorrer.
review_translated_text: Beautiful! Very calm! There was almost no one when we visited, you can do water activities like kayaking. Although, the water seemed colder than in Bahia Brava. There are places to eat in the surrounding area and it is very picturesque to walk around. There is a mini crafts fair, but there are very few stalls. If you rent a bike! Its great to walk around.

review_text: Iniciando el parque nacional, tene en cuenta que hay mucha subida de repente. Incluso cuando estabamos ingresando, bajaba una pareja enojada porque habian llegado hasta el mirador y no se animaron a seguir porque fue demasiado para ellos la subida. No desestimar esto  por eso mucha gente dice que vale la pena el esfuerzo. Si bien el sendero es de nivel bajo, es importante tenerlo en cuenta porque te encontras con miradores tan hermosos como estos que te quedas enamorado de la naturaleza por un buen rato. Nosotros hicimos el dia anterior el cerro y la cascada y tardamos 8 horas, asi que cuando llegamos a este mirador, pudimos ver bien buestro trayecto.
review_translated_text: Starting the national park, keep in mind that there is a lot of sudden climbing. Even when we were entering, an angry couple was coming down because they had reached the viewpoint and they did not dare to continue because the climb was too much for them. Dont underestimate this... thats why many people say its worth the effort. Although the trail is at a low level, it is important to keep it in mind because you will find such beautiful viewpoints like these that you will fall in love with nature for a long time. We did the hill and the waterfall the day before and it took us 8 hours, so when we arrived at this viewpoint, we could see our route well.

review_text: lugar hermoso, muy tranquilo para pasar un rato disfrutando la costa del lago. La unica desventaja es que no hay bajadas accesibles ni accesos a los paseos nauticos que sean aptos para movilidad reducida
review_translated_text: Beautiful, very quiet place to spend some time enjoying the lake coast. The only disadvantage is that there are no accessible descents or access to the nautical tours that are suitable for reduced mobility.

review_text: Precioso lugar a metros del centro de la angostura. Muy linda playa en un entorno increible. Digno de visitar
review_translated_text: Beautiful place meters from the center of La Angostura. Very nice beach in an incredible environment. Worth visiting

review_text: Excelente para la familia!!
review_translated_text: Excellent for the family!!

review_text: Very beautiful and quiet place at sunset. The pier is not as well maintained as it was a few years ago. Small beach. There are pieces of glass between the pebbles. Careful!!! Boats, boats and kayaks leave from there, apparently rented.

Hermosa vista y un lugar de asistencia obligada en SMA. De ahi sale el sendero al bosque de Arrayanes, un camino hermoso que hicimos y que recomiendo si el clima acompana. Despues se puede volver a Bahia mansa en barco desde el puerto en bosque de Arrayanes
review_translated_text: Beautiful view and a must-attend place in SMA. From there comes the path to the Arrayanes forest, a beautiful path that we took and that I recommend if the weather is good. Afterwards you can return to Bahia Mansa by boat from the port in the Arrayanes forest.

review_text: Lindo recorrido para ir en pareja y llegar a tomar lindas fotos el mirador es mejor de lo que imaginan solo hay que estar alli,   La montana   te atrae y hay tanta paz que no quieres dejar el lugar... Tengan cuidado con los insectos    despues de eso solo un paraiso
review_translated_text: Nice tour to go as a couple and get to take nice photos, the viewpoint is better than you imagine, you just have to be there,   The mountain   attracts you and there is so much peace that you dont want to leave the place... Be careful with the insects    after that just a paradise

review_text: Visite el lugar pero me aloje en Bahia Brava que fue un lugar maravilloso, para pasar un dia tranquilo, la playa maravillosa, pero si queres descansar del sol poca sombra
review_translated_text: I visited the place but I stayed in Bahia Brava which was a wonderful place, to spend a quiet day, the beach was wonderful, but if you want to rest from the sun, little shade

review_text: Hermoso lugar!
review_translated_text: Beautiful place!

review_text: De mis lugares favoritos de la villa y que sin duda visito cada ves que voy a La Angostura, su nombre le queda perfecto son contada las veces que en esta playa hay mal tiempo por viento.. espectacular paisaje y lindo espacio para banarse
review_translated_text: One of my favorite places in the town and that I undoubtedly visit every time I go to La Angostura, its name suits it perfectly, there are few times that this beach has bad weather due to wind... spectacular landscape and nice space to bathe

review_text: Bahia mansa es hermoso! El unico problema de ir en temporada es que la playa es muy pequena y se junta mucha gente. Salvo eso es increible. En mi opinion de las mejores vistas del sur desde su muelle. Podes hacer kayak y salir en el catamaran para ver el bosque de Arrayanas. Uno de mis lugares favoritos de Villa.
review_translated_text: Bahia mansa is beautiful! The only problem with going in season is that the beach is very small and a lot of people gather. Except for that its incredible. In my opinion, it has the best views of the south from its pier. You can kayak and go out on the catamaran to see the Arrayanas forest. One of my favorite places in Villa.

review_text: Hermoso paisaje..
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape..

review_text: La fachada del lugar es muy bella, la comida abundante, en el caso de la ensalada de mar el salmon es muy rico y los tres langostinos que trajeron estaban bien logrados de sabor... El precio esta bien por lo que trae el plato
review_translated_text: The facade of the place is very beautiful, the food is abundant, in the case of the sea salad the salmon is very delicious and the three prawns they brought were well done in flavor... The price is good for what the dish comes with

review_text: Very nice bay, ideal to spend a nice day appreciating the beauty of the surroundings. Point to improve, lack of bathrooms and public services, essential in a tourist center.
Linda playa. Agua verde de un lado del muelle y azul del otro. Se alquilan kayaks y botes a pedal. Arena y piedras. Salen los catamaranes al Parque Nacional Arrayanes. Hora de kayak 1500.
review_translated_text: Beautiful beach. Green water on one side of the pier and blue on the other. Kayaks and pedal boats are available for rent. Sand and stones. The catamarans leave for the Arrayanes National Park. Kayak hour 1500.

review_text: El Chalten cuenta con un lugar para que las Motor Home puedan aparcar. Esta antes de cruzar el puente de ingreso al pueblo, enfrente de la oficina de informes. Tiene una linda vista al cerro.
review_translated_text: El Chalten has a place for Motor Homes to park. It is before crossing the bridge entering the town, in front of the information office. It has a nice view of the hill.

review_text: Hermoso!!!! Un lugar divino. Unica critica, si queres tomarte un cafe temprano nada abre hasta las 10 de la manana
review_translated_text: Beautiful!!!! A divine place. Only criticism, if you want to have an early coffee nothing opens until 10 in the morning

review_text: Hermoso paisaje a la orilla del lago. Salen catamaranes hacia el Bosque de Arrayanes. Es un lindo paseo aunque un poco costoso.
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape on the shore of the lake. Catamarans leave for the Arrayanes Forest. It is a nice walk although a little expensive.

review_text: Lugar emblematico no muy concurrido ese dia
review_translated_text: Emblematic place not very crowded that day

review_text: Bonito lugar, pequeno lugar, pero bonito para pasar un rato.
review_translated_text: Nice place, small place, but nice to spend some time.

review_text: Muy linda vista de toda la naturaleza del lugar, una pena el poco mantenimiento y aseo del lugar, pasarelas rotas, sin escalones.
review_translated_text: Very nice view of all the nature of the place, a shame about the lack of maintenance and cleanliness of the place, broken walkways, no steps.

review_text: Muy lindo y tranquilo. La playita es linda y extensa. Estacionar es un tema ya que el lugar no alcanza para la gente que suele ir.
review_translated_text: Very nice and quiet. The beach is beautiful and extensive. Parking is an issue since the place is not enough for the people who usually go.

review_text: Hermoso lugar con unas vistas espectaculares
review_translated_text: Beautiful place with spectacular views

review_text: Un lugar muy bello
review_translated_text: A very beautiful place

review_text: Hermosaaaaa vista! Hermosooo paisaje! Lo malo es que si vas fuera de temporada, artesanos hay 2. Lo lugares pars comer son pocos y laa excursiones no hay muchas opciones a elegir. Pero sin dudas es un bello lugar para conocer si estas en el sur.
review_translated_text: Beautiful view! Beautiful landscape! The bad thing is that if you go out of season, there are 2 artisans. The places to eat are few and for excursions there are not many options to choose from. But without a doubt it is a beautiful place to visit if you are in the south.

review_text: Aguas tranquilas, profundidad de las aguas delimitadas por boyas. Limpieza y excelente vegetacion.
review_translated_text: Calm waters, depth of water delimited by buoys. Cleanliness and excellent vegetation.

review_text: Muy lindo, comidas sencilla y precios razonables, si van a cenar recomiendo reservar con anticipacion
review_translated_text: Very nice, simple meals and reasonable prices, if you are going to dinner I recommend booking in advance

review_text: Hermoso lugar. Vinimos en enero en un dia calido y estaba hermoso para refrescarse y disfrutar del agua.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. We came in January on a warm day and it was beautiful to cool off and enjoy the water.

review_text: Lindo lugar, cuando fuimos estaba cerrada, tuvimos que zarpar desde Bahia Brava
review_translated_text: Nice place, when we went it was closed, we had to sail from Bahia Brava

review_text: Muy bonito lugar para sacar fotos y dar un paseo y es para toda clases de gente ay sale botes a bosques de arayanes
review_translated_text: Very nice place to take photos and take a walk and it is for all kinds of people and there are boats to the arayanes forests

review_text: Beautiful place with spectacular views. Easy access and many places to visit 100%x100% recommended
Hermoso lugar. Muy tranquilo y con muchas actividades para hacer en familia. Recomendable
review_translated_text: Beautiful place. Very quiet and with many activities to do as a family. Recommended

review_text: Lugar encantador
review_translated_text: Enchanting place

review_text: Todo exelente. Me encantaria que sean mas flexiblea con el desayuno. Hay que pedir el dia antes. Y si te vas de excursion o a pasear y no llegas perdiste
review_translated_text: Everything excellent. I would love them to be more flexible with breakfast. You have to order the day before. And if you go on an excursion or for a walk and dont arrive, youve lost.

review_text: Beautiful places like this must be maintained. On this beach, as on others, you see little but at least some garbage and part of that blame is due to the few garbage cans.
Lindo mirador en un entorno natural inigualable. Visita obligada si vas a Villa La Angostura.
review_translated_text: Beautiful viewpoint in a unique natural environment. A must visit if you go to Villa La Angostura.

review_text: Belleza absoluta y mucha paz
review_translated_text: Absolute beauty and a lot of peace

review_text: Super cute. You can even dive. Facing the entry of the PNA. Bathrooms nearby... the bus that says Puerto leaves you from the terminal (below); a divinity

El camino se interrumpe antes del final, por lo que la vista es algo limitada por la vegetacion. Parece que la parte final del camino esta en mal estado y por eso lo interrumpen antes del final. Igualmente en varios puntos del camino hay buena vista de la Bahia Mansa.
review_translated_text: The path is interrupted before the end, so the view is somewhat limited by the vegetation. It seems that the final part of the path is in poor condition and that is why they interrupt it before the end. Likewise, at various points along the way there is a good view of Bahia Mansa.

review_text: Hermoso paisaje y el lugar.
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape and place.

review_text: El recorrido es muy agradable! Hice la idea en el catamaran y la vuelta caminando por el sendero. Super recomendable. Eso si, no olvidar agua y calzado comodo.
review_translated_text: The tour is very pleasant! I did the idea on the catamaran and the return walking along the path. Super recommended. Of course, dont forget water and comfortable shoes.

review_text: Para volver con ropa de playa, almuerzo o merienda en el bolso, llevar bebida, se enfria en el lago jajaja. Reposera o mantita. Si hay viento hace frio si sale el sol malla!!
review_translated_text: To return with beach clothes, lunch or snack in your bag, bring a drink, it gets cold in the lake hahaha. Lounge chair or blanket. If there is wind it is cold if the sun comes out mesh!!

review_text: Lindo lugar para tomar mates y paseos en barco por la bahia
review_translated_text: Nice place to have mates and boat rides in the bay

review_text: Lugar hermoso para disfrutar.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to enjoy.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar y lo mas es que esta muy bien  preservado..
review_translated_text: Very nice place and the best thing is that it is very well preserved.

review_text: Bello lugar, un paisaje precioso.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, beautiful landscape.

review_text: Muy lindo para ir a pasar un rato; o una jornada
review_translated_text: Very nice to go spend some time; or a day

review_text: Bello lugar , muy familiar. Poco espacio para estacionar
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, very familiar. Little parking space

review_text: Hermosas playas y el trekking a los miradores vale la pena para apreciar las 2 bahias
review_translated_text: Beautiful beaches and trekking to the viewpoints are worth it to appreciate the 2 bays

review_text: Un lugar magico.  Increible paisaje para disfrutar con amigos o en familia
review_translated_text: A magical place. Incredible landscape to enjoy with friends or family

review_text: Lugar muy tranquilo, cuando es epoca que no hay turistas.
review_translated_text: Very quiet place, when there are no tourists.

review_text: Hermoso lugar...
review_translated_text: Beautiful place...

review_text: Nice, extensive beach! The water is smooth for kayaking and getting in calmly.
Excelente playa para estar en familia , tranquila , podes realizar actividades en barco . Super recomendable para una tarde en villa la angostura .
review_translated_text: Excellent beach to be with the family, quiet, you can do boat activities. Super recommended for an afternoon in Villa La Angostura.

review_text: Hermoso, lugar y muy buena vista , vale la pena 100%
review_translated_text: Beautiful place and very good view, 100% worth it

review_text: Hermoso lugar, lindo paseo, pero no tiene una buena oferta gastronomica, cuidado con los precios, el unico que safa es el restaurant del puerto.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place, nice walk, but it does not have a good gastronomic offer, be careful with the prices, the only one that is safe is the restaurant at the port.

review_text: La lluvia hizo que la bahia y el muelle estuvieran poco concurrido y esto ayudo a que se pudieran ver algunas aves como macas y cauquenes en la orilla y en el lago.
review_translated_text: The rain meant that the bay and the pier were not very crowded and this helped to see some birds such as macas and cauquenes on the shore and in the lake.

review_text: Lugar muy tranquilo, con algunos restaurantes frente a la Bahia. Precios un poco caros, para mi gusto.
review_translated_text: Very quiet place, with some restaurants facing the Bay. Prices a little expensive, for my taste.

review_text: Hermoso Lugar, una pena que le haya sido entregado a los pueblos originarios y los argentinos no podamos ingresar libremente nunca mas.  Se esta llenando de viviendas particulares.
review_translated_text: Beautiful Place, a shame that it has been handed over to the native peoples and we Argentines cannot enter freely again. It is filling up with private homes.

review_text: Beautiful place! You have to be moderately prepared for the walk. It is long and uphill through beautiful places and views.
La vista maravillosa el camino es cansador pero no imposible despacio lo subis y vale la pena.
review_translated_text: The view is wonderful, the path is tiring but not impossible, slowly you climb it and it is worth it.

review_text: Lindo lugar, hermosa playa. Le excursion lacustre a Bosque de arrayanes estuvo buena, muy interesante la visita guiada
review_translated_text: Nice place, beautiful beach. The lake excursion to Arrayanes Forest was good, the guided tour was very interesting

review_text: Just look at the view , it speaks for itself
Hermosa vista. Pero habia mucho viento. No me quede.
review_translated_text: Beautiful view. But there was a lot of wind. I didnt stay.

review_text: Muy lindas las vistas
review_translated_text: Very nice views

review_text: Poco tiempo de sol
review_translated_text: little time of sun

review_text: Beautiful landscape. I couldnt enjoy it because it was a rainy day. I would like to return in summer
Recomiendo pasear en catamaran hasta el bosque de arrayanes y luego venir caminando, son 12 ks. Aprox 3 hs
review_translated_text: I recommend taking a catamaran ride to the myrtle forest and then walking, it is 12 ks. Approximately 3 hours

review_text: Hermosa bahia! Increible el color del agua. Hay Kayak y otras actividades para hacer.
review_translated_text: Beautiful bay! Incredible color of the water. There is Kayaking and other activities to do.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar para, pasear
review_translated_text: Very nice place to walk

review_text: Hermoso lugar para pasar el dia.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place to spend the day.

review_text: Una panoramica muy linda. Si se llega hasta alli conviene visitar tambien el otro mirador.
review_translated_text: A very nice panorama. If you get there, you should also visit the other viewpoint.

review_text: Hermoso lugar... Muy recomendable para ir
review_translated_text: Beautiful place... Highly recommended to go

review_text: Un hermoso lugar para compartir en familia!! Limpio tranquilo con mucha paz!!
review_translated_text: A beautiful place to share with the family!! Clean quiet with a lot of peace!!

review_text: Hermoso lugar para esparcimiento. El estacionamamiento complicado y mucha suciedad por todos lados. Es una lastima por ser un lugar muy turistico.
review_translated_text: Beautiful place for recreation. Difficult parking and a lot of dirt everywhere. Its a shame because its a very touristy place.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar....falta cuidar mas las banquinas, mantener limpias y parejas.... En todas partes d las rutas
review_translated_text: Very nice place...we need to take more care of the shoulders, keep them clean and even.... Everywhere on the routes

review_text: Hermosa, recomendable el sendero del rio bonito, la desembocadura es muy bella y el entorno inmejorable...
review_translated_text: Beautiful, the beautiful river path is recommended, the mouth is very beautiful and the environment is unbeatable...

review_text: Hermoso espacio recreativo con salida a las dos orillas
review_translated_text: Beautiful recreational space with access to both shores

review_text: Es un lugar perfecto tiene un paisaje increible las instalaciones son excelentes. La comida le falta un poquito
review_translated_text: It is a perfect place, it has an incredible landscape, the facilities are excellent. The food is a little lacking

review_text: Bahia Mansa aporta un paisaje enamorante, pintoresco y relajante. Tiene lindos paseos en bote al bosque arrayanes y a otros lugares. Es necesario que estes aqui si quieres ver un lindo paisaje
review_translated_text: Bahia Mansa provides an enchanting, picturesque and relaxing landscape. It has nice boat rides to the myrtle forest and other places. You need to be here if you want to see a beautiful landscape

review_text: Hermosa como siempre, solo q comer es carisimo, por muy baja calidad.
review_translated_text: Beautiful as always, its just that eating is very expensive, due to very low quality.

review_text: Muy lindo lugar! Pero en algunos lugares donde todo deberia ser naturaleza! Te encontras con restos de basura! Cuidemos por favor!

review_text: Very nice free tour in Villa Angostura. It is possible to take a light trail to viewpoints overlooking Nahuel Huapi Lake with beautiful views. It is possible to take a boat to visit the Ahayanes forest that leaves at 11 am or 2:30 pm (if Im not mistaken). If you are staying in Bariloche, the road itself is an attraction, with beautiful views of the lake and mountain ranges and preserved vegetation.
review_translated_text: Passeio gratuito muito agradavel em Villa Angostura. E possivel fazer uma trilha leve ate mirantes para o lago Nahuel Huapi com vistas lindas. E possivel pegar um barco para visitar o bosque de Ahayanes que sai as 11 ou as 14:30 (se nao me engano). Se voce esta hospedado em Bariloche, a estrada por si so e um atrativo, com belas vistas do lago e das cordilheiras e vegetacao preservada.

review_text: Calm, peaceful place that transmits a lot of peace!! Its worth taking a boat trip and having a coffee or a beer while enjoying the view. Whoever is in Angostura go!!
Place with a fantastic view, nearby there is a local craft fair and nearby, inside a park, there is a very cool trail.

review_text: Muy lindo el lugar fuimos a arrayanes - lamento la noticia esta casi todo seco no vale la pena - habria que dejar de ir para que el organismo correspondiente se ocupe de recuperar el bosque

review_text: Lindo paseo para caminar cerca del muelle y los negocios de artesanos. Hay poco espacio para estacionar por la tarde.
review_translated_text: Nice promenade to walk near the pier and the artisan businesses. There is little parking space in the afternoon.

review_text: Linda vista a mitad de camino. Pero si es por las vistas no vale la pena seguir el camino mas alla de esas vistas. El final del camino no tiene vistas lindas, pero se llega a la roca del acantilado que se ve enorme vista desde abajo.
review_translated_text: Nice view halfway up. But if its for the views its not worth continuing the path beyond those views. The end of the path does not have nice views, but you reach the cliff rock that looks enormous from below.

review_text: En el puerto angostura se pueden realizar viajes en barco al bosque dearrayanes
review_translated_text: In the Angostura port you can take boat trips to the Arrayanes forest.

review_text: Un lugar encantador a la vista
review_translated_text: A lovely place to look at

review_text: Excellent view of the lake.... Very rich and abundant red fruit smoothie
Many dogs, baskets without bags, excess papers and waste. The place is very beautiful.
Muy lindo lugar para conocer, disfrutar del dia, habia feria de artesanos, pero los banos eran horribles, cero mantenimiento y limpieza.
review_translated_text: Very nice place to meet, enjoy the day, there was an artisan fair, but the bathrooms were horrible, zero maintenance and cleaning.

review_text: Hermoso paisaje, con un muelle y playa donde se puede disfrutar del agua o sacar fotografias sorprendentes
review_translated_text: Beautiful landscape, with a pier and beach where you can enjoy the water or take amazing photographs

review_text: Nice place to kayak. The beach more or less. The water is just as cold as the others in the area and has a strong fishy smell from the boats moored there.
Muy lindo paisaje pero muy descuidado por parque nacional muy sucio y nada mantenimiento sendero
review_translated_text: Very nice landscape but very neglected due to a very dirty national park and no trail maintenance

review_text: Para sacar fotos en el muelle esta bien. Pero no para hacer playa. La brava esta mucho mejor. Demasiadas embarcaciones.
review_translated_text: To take photos on the dock is fine. But not to go to the beach. The brava is much better. Too many boats.

review_text: Linda, pero encontre sucia la playa, faltan tachos de residuos y personal que se ocupe se mantenerla mas limpia.
review_translated_text: Nice, but I found the beach dirty, there is a lack of waste bins and staff to keep it cleaner.

review_text: Muchas gente y poca organizacion, hasta tardaron para vendernos el pase para el parque los alerces, vi varios extranjeros enojados yendose del lugar.
review_translated_text: Many people and little organization, they even took a while to sell us the pass to the Los Alerces park, I saw several angry foreigners leaving the place.

review_text: The prices are normal. They offer you a plate for 2 and they come with little flavor. You should eat more calmly

El muelle se cae a pedazos le falta mantenimiento. Solo colocaron un cinta de peligro. Todos los anos qie voy de visita esta igual. El municipio no se arremanga la camisa para trabajar nunca. Los catamaranes no respetan a otras embarcaciones. Vimos mucha espuma jabonosa en la bahia por la contaminacion de los sanitarios.
review_translated_text: The dock is falling apart and lacks maintenance. They just put up some danger tape. Every year I visit it is the same. The municipality never rolls up its sleeves to work. Catamarans do not respect other boats. We saw a lot of soapy foam in the bay due to the contamination of the toilets.

review_text: Hermosa Playa de Bariloche. En km 12. De la ruta Bustillo
review_translated_text: Beautiful Bariloche Beach. At km 12. From the Bustillo route

review_text: El lugar, como todo en Angostura, es paradisiaco. Lamentablemente, como tantas otras playas de Angostura, no permite perros, pero si gente con parlantes a todo lo que de quebrando toda la paz del lugar.
review_translated_text: The place, like everything in Angostura, is heavenly. Unfortunately, like so many other beaches in Angostura, it does not allow dogs, but it does allow people with loud speakers, breaking all the peace of the place.

review_text: Es una playa linda, el paisaje lo es, pero no fue de las que mas me gusto en villa la angostura
review_translated_text: It is a beautiful beach, the landscape is, but it was not one of the ones I liked the most in Villa La Angostura

review_text: Un lugar pintoresco y tambien con hermosos paisajes, pero me gusto mas Villa La Angostura.
review_translated_text: A picturesque place and also with beautiful landscapes, but I liked Villa La Angostura better.

review_text: La playa esta sucia y desprolijo. Por ser un lugar  q esta en el casco del pueblo tendria q estar mucho mejor y cuidado. Desde el punto de vista naturales  es hermoso  y el agua de color verde es muy linda.

From a natural point of view it is beautiful and the green water is very pretty.

review_text: Lindo lugar, buena atencion. No habia chocolate caliente, el bano estaba clausurado y no tenian servilletas. Parecia que no estaba listo para atender. Lo que comi tenia mas pinta que gusto pero para una merienda cualquiera, sirve.
review_translated_text: Nice place, good service. There was no hot chocolate, the bathroom was closed and they had no napkins. It seemed like he wasnt ready to attend. What I ate looked more like it than it tasted, but for any snack, it works.

review_text: En el momento que lo visitamos (enero 2019) estaba cortado el paso al mirador. Y no habia una explicacion. La playa La Mansa esta envuelta de pinos altos q protegen de los vientos;el agua cristalina y quieta; la arena gruesa y clara.
review_translated_text: At the time we visited (January 2019) the access to the viewpoint was blocked. And there was no explanation. La Mansa beach is surrounded by tall pine trees that protect from the winds; the crystal clear and still water; the thick and clear sand.

review_text: Es bastante tranquilo. No encontre una Costanera para sentarse a tomar mate o cualquier cosa al pie del lago.
review_translated_text: Its pretty quiet. I didnt find a Costanera to sit and drink mate or anything at the foot of the lake.

review_text: Un lugar que no vale la pena. A raiz de la pandemia esta todo cerrado, lo unico para ver un altar con la virgencita, y por supuesto el paisaje
review_translated_text: A place that is not worth it. Due to the pandemic, everything is closed, the only thing to see is an altar with the little virgin, and of course the landscape

review_text: Lo unico malo que no habia banos publicos como van a clausurar banos sin habilitar los nuevos
review_translated_text: The only bad thing was that there were no public bathrooms, how are they going to close bathrooms without enabling new ones?

review_text: Los platos son ricos pero la atencion es muy lenta, los precios estandar ni muy altos ni economicos.
review_translated_text: The dishes are delicious but the service is very slow, the standard prices are neither very high nor cheap.

review_text: Caro. Hay otros locales cercanos con misma calidad.
review_translated_text: Expensive. There are other places nearby with the same quality.

review_text: Paz, belleza y tranquilidad!!!! Que mas se puede pedir

review_text: Mucha vegetacion... Poca vista al lago.
